00:48.480 --> 00:50.369
[CHILD SHOUTING IN XHOSA]

01:10.720 --> 01:13.087
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

01:19.960 --> 01:23.043
<i>[Mandela] I dream the same dream</i>

01:23.200 --> 01:25.601
<i>night after night.</i>

01:26.920 --> 01:31.687
<i>I am coming home
to the house in Orlando.</i>

01:31.840 --> 01:34.923
<i>Everything is the way it was.</i>

01:41.840 --> 01:43.524
<i>They are all there.</i>

01:44.560 --> 01:49.691
<i>All the ones that I have loved
most in the world.</i>

01:51.560 --> 01:53.050
[LAUGHTER ECHOING]

01:53.200 --> 01:58.161
<i>They seem fine,
getting on with their lives.</i>

02:01.640 --> 02:05.929
<i>But they do not see me.</i>

02:06.080 --> 02:08.002
<i>They never see me.</i>

02:14.800 --> 02:17.531
<i>[CHILDREN'S SHOUTS ECHOING]</i>

02:23.680 --> 02:25.648
[TRIBAL MUSIC PLAYING]

02:45.800 --> 02:48.724
[SHOUTING IN XHOSA]

03:18.000 --> 03:20.651
[CHANTING IN XHOSA]

03:22.880 --> 03:24.882
[MAN] Your youth,

03:25.040 --> 03:27.042
your beauty,

03:27.200 --> 03:30.966
your strength
is not yours to hold.

03:33.960 --> 03:36.770
You alone are small,

03:36.920 --> 03:39.207
your people are mighty.

03:40.440 --> 03:42.204
Now go!

03:42.360 --> 03:44.681
You are a man.

03:44.840 --> 03:47.286
Leave as a man!

03:52.840 --> 03:56.003
<i>[MANDELA] Now I was a man</i>

03:56.160 --> 03:58.686
<i>with duties to my people.</i>

03:59.920 --> 04:03.367
<i>My father had given me
the name Rolihlahla...</i>

04:03.520 --> 04:04.806
<i>troublemaker.</i>

04:06.360 --> 04:09.330
<i>I didn't want to make trouble.</i>

04:09.480 --> 04:13.849
<i>I wanted to make
my family proud of me.</i>

04:14.000 --> 04:16.651
[UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING]

04:34.160 --> 04:36.208
[SPEAKING IN AFRICAN LANGUAGE]

04:54.640 --> 04:57.120
[WOMEN LAUGHING]

04:58.840 --> 05:00.808
[LAUGHING]

05:00.960 --> 05:02.962
[HORN HONKING]

05:03.120 --> 05:04.406
Out of the way, boy.

05:04.560 --> 05:06.642
[MAN] Stop, Kaffir.

05:06.800 --> 05:08.882
- [MAN 2] Come on, Kaffir.
- [MAN 3] Yes, sir.

05:09.040 --> 05:11.202
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

05:12.800 --> 05:14.484
[MANDELA] Sorry, sorry.

05:18.400 --> 05:19.640
Court in 15 minutes.

05:19.840 --> 05:20.961
- Fifteen?
- Fifteen minutes.

05:21.000 --> 05:23.606
- Mr. Mandela, sir, you promised us.
- Yes, yes.

05:23.800 --> 05:25.848
But the people are losing hope
in their land.

05:26.000 --> 05:28.207
How can I help you?

05:28.360 --> 05:30.362
I am not a thief.

05:32.280 --> 05:36.490
Mrs. De Kock, my client,

05:36.640 --> 05:38.881
your former maid, has been accused

05:39.040 --> 05:41.646
of stealing these items
of clothing from your bedroom.

05:42.800 --> 05:44.802
Am I to be spoken to like this
by a native?

05:44.960 --> 05:47.406
He is counsel
for the defense, ma'am,

05:47.560 --> 05:50.040
but if you feel uncomfortable,

05:50.240 --> 05:52.288
you may address your answers to me.

05:52.440 --> 05:54.283
Thank you, Your Worship.

05:54.440 --> 05:56.044
Mrs. De Kock, how do we know

05:56.200 --> 05:59.488
that these items are not
my client's herself?

06:00.480 --> 06:02.528
I don't understand.
What is he saying?

06:02.680 --> 06:04.523
Well, what I am saying is

06:04.680 --> 06:10.801
can you identify these items
as yours, Mrs. De Kock?

06:11.680 --> 06:14.570
Well, you seem... unsure.

06:15.320 --> 06:19.041
I will not be spoken to like this,
it's disgusting.

06:19.200 --> 06:21.600
If I'd known I was going to be
so insulted in a court of law,

06:21.680 --> 06:23.523
I would never have come.

06:24.120 --> 06:26.487
Your Honor, I move that...

06:26.640 --> 06:30.281
Yes, yes. Case dismissed.

06:30.440 --> 06:33.523
[SIGHS, CROWD MURMURING]

06:35.400 --> 06:37.687
Siyabonga,
you must carry my bag here.

06:37.840 --> 06:39.842
- You are lazy.
- Madiba?

06:40.040 --> 06:41.963
I hear you're a man to watch.

06:42.120 --> 06:44.122
Maybe I should sell tickets.

06:45.160 --> 06:46.889
You don't come to
Congress meetings.

06:47.040 --> 06:48.326
Why would I want to do that?

06:48.480 --> 06:49.641
Well, do you know
anything about us?

06:49.840 --> 06:51.960
You know anything about
the African National Congress?

06:52.040 --> 06:54.122
If you went out today
and said, "Follow me,"

06:54.280 --> 06:56.408
nobody would follow you,
so why should I?

06:56.600 --> 06:59.206
Do you like it when the Boers
are calling you "boy"?

06:59.360 --> 07:01.601
[CHUCKLES]
When I am better qualified

07:01.760 --> 07:04.366
and better dressed and
richer than they are,

07:04.520 --> 07:06.010
they won't call me boy anymore.

07:06.160 --> 07:08.481
- Baleka!
- [CHUCKLES]

07:09.360 --> 07:12.364
You're right. We need him.

07:12.520 --> 07:15.251
[WOMAN SINGING IN AFRICAN LANGUAGE]

07:25.360 --> 07:27.488
[WOMAN] What does a hotshot
lawyer know that I don't know?

07:27.640 --> 07:30.166
[MANDELA] I know that the law says
you can only have relations

07:30.320 --> 07:32.891
with members of your own race.

07:33.040 --> 07:34.644
Am I a member of your own race?

07:34.800 --> 07:36.404
- Mr. Jackson.
- Pencil test. [LAUGHING]

07:36.600 --> 07:40.571
See, this is the official method
of establishing racial type.

07:40.720 --> 07:43.041
The pencil stays in my hair.

07:43.200 --> 07:44.804
I am a black man.

07:44.960 --> 07:47.167
- Now me?
- Hm...

07:48.080 --> 07:50.811
The pencil stays in your hair.

07:50.960 --> 07:54.726
You are black and can officially
have relations with me.

07:54.880 --> 07:56.405
[CHUCKLING]

08:03.160 --> 08:05.731
- Always works.
- [JACKSON LAUGHS]

08:08.560 --> 08:13.521
- [SINGING CONTINUES]
- [INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

08:20.400 --> 08:23.051
My darling, my darling.

08:23.200 --> 08:25.202
You must wear my jacket.

08:25.400 --> 08:27.846
Then I can steal a kiss.

08:28.000 --> 08:29.889
Yeah, yeah,
it's you that I want to see!

08:30.040 --> 08:31.610
- You?
- Yeah, see you, my friend.

08:31.760 --> 08:33.720
This one, you take her home, my man.
She's lovely.

08:33.760 --> 08:35.568
Are you going to be fine, yeah?

08:35.720 --> 08:37.927
- Never better.
- How many fingers?

08:38.120 --> 08:39.804
[LAUGHTER]

08:39.960 --> 08:41.485
Ah!

08:41.640 --> 08:43.130
Bye!

08:43.280 --> 08:45.169
[MUTTERING]

08:46.600 --> 08:48.125
Hey, you!

08:48.280 --> 08:49.202
I said you!

08:49.360 --> 08:51.567
- Hey?
- Where's your pass, eh?

08:52.440 --> 08:53.771
Ah... Oh.

08:53.920 --> 08:56.400
- I left it at home, boss.
- No, no, no, no, no.

08:56.560 --> 08:57.686
You come with me, come on.

08:57.840 --> 08:59.968
Hey, don't put up a fight.
Come with me.

09:02.760 --> 09:05.161
- Come, boy.
- That's right. Out you come.

09:06.640 --> 09:08.483
[MUTTERING]

09:09.960 --> 09:12.611
The kaffir's got no pass,
so we're gonna put him in a cell.

09:12.760 --> 09:15.411
- Let's go.
- Come on, Kaffir.

09:15.560 --> 09:16.721
- Get up, get up,
- Get up!

09:16.880 --> 09:17.802
Get up.

09:17.960 --> 09:19.166
[RETCHES]

09:19.320 --> 09:20.765
- That's my shoe!
- Kick him, man.

09:20.920 --> 09:23.082
- [GRUNTING]
- [SHOUTING]

09:26.040 --> 09:27.963
That's it, get up.
Get him up.

09:28.120 --> 09:30.043
[JACKSON CHOKING]

09:31.320 --> 09:33.004
<i>[MANDELA] Jackson Glada.</i>

09:33.160 --> 09:35.083
<i>[MAN] Questioned at Jeppe Station.</i>

09:35.240 --> 09:36.526
<i>- [MANDELA] Yes.
- [MAN] No pass.</i>

09:36.720 --> 09:39.405
Cause of death,
congenital syphilis.

09:39.560 --> 09:41.289
Everything is in order here.

09:41.440 --> 09:44.444
No, he was beaten to death
in Jeppe Station.

09:44.640 --> 09:47.246
I have the medical affidavits
for his injuries.

09:47.440 --> 09:49.568
Are you accusing the
police of lying?

09:49.720 --> 09:51.210
I have medical affidavits.

09:51.400 --> 09:55.769
I suggest that you start showing
some respect of the law, boy.

09:55.920 --> 09:58.844
And I have work to do.
Good day to you.

10:01.320 --> 10:02.924
<i>[MANDELA] That's not law.</i>

10:03.120 --> 10:04.565
<i>There's no law for us.</i>

10:05.720 --> 10:07.449
Who did Jackson ever hurt?

10:07.600 --> 10:10.001
I mean, what did he do
to deserve what they did to him?

10:10.160 --> 10:11.241
Thank you.

10:11.400 --> 10:12.761
- And nobody cares.
- [BABY CRYING]

10:12.920 --> 10:14.206
Nobody gives a damn.

10:15.320 --> 10:16.560
Why are you telling me?

10:16.760 --> 10:18.922
Something has to change.

10:19.080 --> 10:24.450
- And how should that happen?
- Education, hard work, pride.

10:24.640 --> 10:27.849
No, no, Nelson,
you can't do it on your own.

10:28.480 --> 10:29.891
None of us can.

10:30.640 --> 10:33.689
That's me, and that's you,

10:33.840 --> 10:35.683
and that's Oliver...

10:36.720 --> 10:38.563
and that's Kathy.

10:38.720 --> 10:41.849
And each one of us are
too little to do anything.

10:42.000 --> 10:43.809
But together...

10:44.880 --> 10:46.041
we have the power.

10:49.640 --> 10:52.246
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS IN DISTANCE]

10:59.000 --> 11:00.081
Smoke?

11:01.280 --> 11:03.009
I don't smoke.

11:09.880 --> 11:12.326
Do you think I should join the ANC?

11:15.520 --> 11:17.568
I think they like to talk.

11:23.480 --> 11:27.041
And what about you?
What do you like to do?

11:29.120 --> 11:30.406
[CHUCKLES]

11:30.560 --> 11:33.643
[UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING]

11:33.800 --> 11:35.529
[HONKING]

11:42.200 --> 11:43.531
[MANDELA] Walter.

11:54.280 --> 11:55.850
[CHUCKLING]

12:05.640 --> 12:07.165
- [WOMAN] Not until we're married.
- [MANDELA] Mm-hm.

12:07.320 --> 12:08.970
[LAUGHTER]

12:11.840 --> 12:13.569
[MEN CHATTERING]

12:13.720 --> 12:15.563
[MAN] Jab, jab.
One, two, ja.

12:16.560 --> 12:17.925
One, two.

12:20.840 --> 12:22.808
Yeah, that's it, very nice.

12:22.960 --> 12:23.927
Come on, chief.

12:24.080 --> 12:25.047
[SPEAKING IN AFRICAN LANGUAGE]

12:25.200 --> 12:26.326
One, two, one, two.

12:26.480 --> 12:28.084
Where's the jab? Where's the jab?

12:30.400 --> 12:31.925
[FIGHTERS GRUNTING]

12:36.680 --> 12:40.571
OK, OK, OK, OK.
All right, OK.

12:42.560 --> 12:44.289
[PANTING]

12:44.440 --> 12:45.851
Walter.

12:46.640 --> 12:47.766
Nelson.

12:48.920 --> 12:50.160
[WALTER]
I see you're working very hard.

12:50.320 --> 12:51.845
[MANDELA] Yes. Must fight.

12:54.040 --> 12:57.169
- Tomorrow morning.
- What's that?

12:57.320 --> 12:59.129
Boycott the buses?

12:59.280 --> 13:01.362
Yeah, you see, you talk
to people about freedom

13:01.520 --> 13:04.251
and justice, they don't listen,

13:04.400 --> 13:08.724
but put their bus fare up by
a penny, that they care about.

13:09.720 --> 13:11.961
[SIGHS]
Help me.

13:12.120 --> 13:13.281
Coach?

13:16.600 --> 13:19.763
- Let me see.
- There we go.

13:22.280 --> 13:24.681
- Bring your new wife.
- [CHUCKLES]

13:39.400 --> 13:41.129
Nelson, you can't work all night.

13:43.160 --> 13:45.049
I'm going to bed now.

13:47.400 --> 13:51.007
- I'll come later.
- You need to give yourself a rest.

13:52.280 --> 13:53.805
You can't do everything.

13:54.880 --> 13:56.086
Leave some things to God.

13:57.080 --> 13:59.242
Does your god want your
children to go hungry?

14:00.280 --> 14:01.202
Nelson...

14:01.400 --> 14:03.971
I don't see your god
caring for our people.

14:05.720 --> 14:07.927
Seems to me that
he is looking after the Boers.

14:08.080 --> 14:09.525
- Nelson...
- [THUMPS]

14:09.680 --> 14:11.125
Evelyn, go to bed.

14:12.720 --> 14:13.881
Go to bed.

14:21.600 --> 14:24.490
<i>[BUS ENGINE RUMBLING]</i>

14:30.200 --> 14:33.249
[WALTER] Let the buses run empty!

14:33.400 --> 14:35.528
Don't pay!

14:35.680 --> 14:38.331
We won't pay a penny more!

14:38.520 --> 14:40.602
We cannot pay a penny more!

14:40.760 --> 14:41.886
[MAN] Shut them down.

14:42.040 --> 14:43.280
[MAN 2] Get you on these buses!

14:44.080 --> 14:47.880
This is the last chance you have
to get on board the buses!

14:48.040 --> 14:51.010
The buses will be leaving
in five minutes!

14:51.200 --> 14:54.966
Don't pay!
Let their buses run empty!

14:55.160 --> 14:56.400
Don't listen to this man!

14:56.560 --> 14:59.723
If we stand together,
we can beat them.

14:59.880 --> 15:01.006
[MAN] This man is a troublemaker!

15:01.160 --> 15:03.527
[WALTER]
We cannot pay a penny more!

15:03.680 --> 15:05.489
Let's not pay!

15:05.640 --> 15:07.563
Let us walk to Johannesburg!

15:10.400 --> 15:12.641
<i>- [WALTER] ¡Afrika!
- [ALL] Mayibuye!</i>

15:12.800 --> 15:16.691
[SINGING IN AFRICAN LANGUAGE]

15:22.680 --> 15:25.047
There's going to be trouble.
I want to go home.

15:38.880 --> 15:43.886
I'm going with them.
They're not breaking any laws.

15:44.040 --> 15:46.202
- But I must go with them.
- Nelson...

15:47.200 --> 15:48.531
You'll be fine.

15:56.800 --> 15:58.564
Ah... [CHUCKLES]

15:58.720 --> 16:00.961
[SINGING CONTINUES]

16:21.440 --> 16:23.920
[NEWS FANFARE PLAYS]

16:25.800 --> 16:28.640
<i>[MALE ANNOUNCER] The Nationalist Party
of Prime Minister Daniel F. Malan</i>

16:28.800 --> 16:30.928
<i>has been returned to power
in the recent election...</i>

16:31.080 --> 16:33.560
<i>[REPORTER] ...the government intends
to geographically separate</i>

16:33.600 --> 16:36.763
<i>the blacks from the whites.
Total enforced segregation.</i>

16:36.920 --> 16:38.763
<i>[REPORTER 2] ...the new Cabinet
has pledged to a policy</i>

16:38.920 --> 16:40.763
<i>of uncompromising white supremacy.</i>

16:40.920 --> 16:43.048
[CHILDREN CHATTERING]

16:44.080 --> 16:46.970
[CHATTER, LAUGHTER]

16:48.720 --> 16:51.121
Ah, Thembi, this is your new home.

16:51.320 --> 16:53.448
- We're calling for freedom of movement.
- No, no, no.

16:54.040 --> 16:57.601
<i>[WALTER] Each campaign volunteer
chooses which forbidden place to enter.</i>

16:57.760 --> 17:00.525
Whites-only post office
and whites-only toilets.

17:00.680 --> 17:02.523
<i>And in the townships,</i>

17:02.680 --> 17:07.049
<i>we cannot tolerate this constant
oppressive military presence.</i>

17:07.200 --> 17:08.645
[EVELYN] Come here, Thembi.

17:08.839 --> 17:10.922
[CLAMORING]

17:12.160 --> 17:14.845
<i>[MANDELA] Why should we
obey their laws?</i>

17:15.000 --> 17:16.843
We don't have a vote.

17:17.000 --> 17:18.888
This is not our government.

17:19.040 --> 17:22.646
They are having a party,
and we are not invited.

17:22.800 --> 17:23.722
[CROWD MURMURS IN AGREEMENT]

17:23.880 --> 17:26.565
So let's defy their unjust laws.

17:26.720 --> 17:29.451
What can they do,
throw us all in prison?

17:29.600 --> 17:31.170
- No.
- Let them.

17:31.360 --> 17:35.126
When we are all in prison,
let them mine their own gold,

17:35.320 --> 17:37.721
- clean their own houses...
- [LAUGHTER]

17:37.880 --> 17:40.167
wash their own clothes.

17:41.000 --> 17:42.411
Thank you for listening.

17:42.840 --> 17:45.764
Thank you. Thank you.
Thank you.

17:49.000 --> 17:50.923
Don't go to prison yet, Nelson.

18:06.000 --> 18:08.048
[DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE]

18:15.400 --> 18:16.811
[WHISPERS] My sweet.

18:20.880 --> 18:22.644
[SIGHS]

18:23.200 --> 18:26.283
- You think I don't know?
- Know what?

18:29.440 --> 18:32.171
Evelyn, it's the defiance campaign.

18:32.920 --> 18:34.285
I'm doing it for all of us.

18:34.440 --> 18:37.171
Yes, you care about all the children
of South Africa except your own.

18:37.320 --> 18:38.321
Hey, hey...

18:38.480 --> 18:39.891
[EVELYN] Are you seeing
other women for them?

18:40.040 --> 18:41.166
Are you seeing your
whores for them?!

18:41.320 --> 18:42.731
- 'Cause I know, Nelson!
- Evelyn...

18:42.880 --> 18:44.564
- And I won't take it anymore!
- Evelyn, stop this now!

18:44.720 --> 18:48.327
- You will burn in Hell!
- Shut your mouth!

18:48.520 --> 18:49.851
- [CLATTERING]
- Shut your mouth.

18:50.000 --> 18:50.922
[EVELYN SCREAMING]

18:51.080 --> 18:53.924
- Shut your stupid mouth.
- [EVELYN CRYING]

18:54.080 --> 18:56.401
- [SIGHING]
- [BABY CRYING]

18:57.480 --> 18:59.960
- Thembi, go to bed.
- [EVELYN CONTINUES CRYING]

19:02.480 --> 19:05.689
We can't do this.
I'm sorry.

19:06.400 --> 19:08.209
[CHEERING, WHISTLING]

19:08.360 --> 19:10.328
<i>[MANDELA] Thulani. Thulani.</i>

19:11.320 --> 19:14.130
The Boers say Sophiatown is a slum.

19:14.280 --> 19:15.202
[JEERING]

19:15.360 --> 19:19.524
All the people that have homes there
are to be evicted by force.

19:19.720 --> 19:21.768
[CROWD SHOUTING]

19:21.920 --> 19:26.244
Sophiatown is to be bulldozed
so they can build houses for the rich.

19:26.400 --> 19:28.323
[CROWD SHOUTING]

19:29.840 --> 19:32.127
Let them try.

19:32.280 --> 19:34.681
We say, "Over our dead bodies."

19:34.840 --> 19:36.490
[CROWD CHEERING]

19:36.640 --> 19:38.449
Let them bring their bulldozers.

19:39.000 --> 19:43.005
Let them bring their army.
We will fight for our homes!

19:43.200 --> 19:44.611
[CROWD CHEERING]

19:44.760 --> 19:47.286
We will fight for our freedom!

19:47.440 --> 19:49.044
[CHEERING]

19:49.200 --> 19:51.885
If they want a war...

19:52.080 --> 19:54.606
we will give them a war.
- [CHEERING]

19:57.400 --> 19:59.448
<i>- Mayibuye!
- [CROWD] ¡Afrika!</i>

19:59.600 --> 20:01.170
<i>- ¡Afrika!
- [CROWD] Mayibuye!</i>

20:01.320 --> 20:03.209
<i>- Mayibuye!
- [CROWD] ¡Afrika!</i>

20:03.360 --> 20:05.089
<i>- ¡Afrika!
- [CROWD] Mayibuye!</i>

20:05.240 --> 20:06.765
[CROWD'S SHOUTS FADING]

20:06.920 --> 20:09.685
[MANDELA] This way! Together!

20:09.840 --> 20:12.241
- [WALTER] Follow Madiba!
- [POLICEMAN] Whites only!

20:15.840 --> 20:17.251
All together, come!

20:37.520 --> 20:39.170
- In there.
- [KATHY] They're coming!

20:39.320 --> 20:40.810
Get them! Come on!

20:42.000 --> 20:44.128
They are coming, they are coming.

20:44.280 --> 20:46.248
[POLICEMAN] Where are they?
Where are they?

20:46.400 --> 20:47.401
What do you think you're doing?

20:47.600 --> 20:49.762
- See, lady, no manners at all.
- Come! Get up!

20:49.920 --> 20:53.129
[KATHY] Let go!
Get your hands off me.

20:53.280 --> 20:54.930
- Sorry, ladies.
- [SHOUTING]

20:55.080 --> 20:57.082
[DOOR SLAMS, ECHOING]

20:57.240 --> 20:59.481
<i>[WALTER]
Together we will beat them!</i>

20:59.640 --> 21:02.689
<i>Together we have power!</i>

21:02.840 --> 21:05.207
<i>- Mayibuye!
- [CROWD] ¡Afrika!</i>

21:05.360 --> 21:07.840
<i>- [WALTER] ¡Afrika!
- [CROWD] Mayibuye!</i>

21:08.000 --> 21:10.924
<i>- [WALTER] Mayibuye!
- [CROWD] ¡Afrika!</i>

21:11.120 --> 21:14.602
<i>- [WALTER] ¡Afrika!
- [CROWD] Mayibuye!</i>

21:14.760 --> 21:17.127
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]
- [CHILDREN SINGING]

21:27.200 --> 21:28.850
[LATCH CLICKING]

21:48.520 --> 21:52.684
- Are you here alone?
- Yes.

21:54.240 --> 21:56.322
Mum doesn't know I'm here.

22:01.280 --> 22:04.489
Mum says we're not
to live with you anymore.

22:05.000 --> 22:08.447
Thembi, I know
that I've been away a lot.

22:10.920 --> 22:13.651
Too much.

22:13.800 --> 22:17.202
But... I'm doing it for all of us.

22:18.200 --> 22:20.806
I want you to believe that.

22:32.640 --> 22:34.802
[SIGHS]

22:40.280 --> 22:42.169
[CHILDREN LAUGH]

22:50.320 --> 22:52.607
[INDISTINCT CHATTER IN DISTANCE]

23:03.640 --> 23:05.961
[CHUCKLES] Hambani. Hambani.

23:06.120 --> 23:09.283
- [MAN] Madiba.
- Mama.

23:09.440 --> 23:10.885
[CHICKEN CLUCKING]

23:25.880 --> 23:27.689
[SPEAKING IN XHOSA]

24:29.000 --> 24:30.764
[SIGHING]

25:03.800 --> 25:05.211
Do you want a lift?

25:06.720 --> 25:09.644
- OK.
- Sure.

25:11.560 --> 25:14.803
Do you always accept lifts
from strangers?

25:14.960 --> 25:18.362
[LAUGHS SOFTLY]
You are not a stranger.

25:18.520 --> 25:20.727
You are Nelson Mandela.

25:20.880 --> 25:23.690
And you are Winnie Madikizela.

25:23.840 --> 25:27.287
- How do you know?
- I made inquiries.

25:27.440 --> 25:29.727
And what else did you find out?

25:29.920 --> 25:32.400
That you work at
Baragwanath Hospital,

25:32.560 --> 25:36.281
you are the first black
social worker they've ever had,

25:36.440 --> 25:39.330
and you're the most beautiful
girl I've ever seen.

25:49.800 --> 25:51.529
[WINNIE] It's just here.

25:55.000 --> 25:56.411
Thank you.

25:59.000 --> 26:00.240
What time do you finish?

26:02.600 --> 26:06.002
- 6:00.
- I'll be here.

26:15.920 --> 26:20.244
You know, I've been finding
out about you, too.

26:20.400 --> 26:22.004
- Yeah?
- Mm-hm.

26:22.160 --> 26:24.686
And what have you found out?

26:24.840 --> 26:26.569
Your wife left you.

26:29.440 --> 26:31.283
I was away too much.

26:32.600 --> 26:34.807
Never enough time.

26:34.960 --> 26:37.281
There is no time.

26:37.440 --> 26:38.930
- Only now.
- Only now?

26:39.080 --> 26:43.244
- Yes.
- [CHUCKLES] What do you mean?

26:43.400 --> 26:46.370
When I was seven years old,

26:46.520 --> 26:50.445
my little sister
started coughing blood.

26:50.600 --> 26:52.887
And my mother, she...

26:53.040 --> 26:55.520
she begged God to save her.

26:57.120 --> 27:00.363
But she died.

27:00.520 --> 27:03.126
And ever since then, I've known

27:03.280 --> 27:06.762
we have to save ourselves,

27:06.920 --> 27:09.810
and we have to live while we can.

27:09.960 --> 27:12.566
- [CHUCKLES]
- [LAUGHS]

27:33.520 --> 27:36.046
Winnie, Winnie.

27:43.760 --> 27:46.684
I heard you have a
lot of girlfriends.

27:48.800 --> 27:50.564
I'm different.

28:06.880 --> 28:09.360
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATION]

28:47.800 --> 28:51.407
I was thinking,
I know a good dressmaker.

28:51.560 --> 28:53.369
Very good value.

28:53.520 --> 28:56.000
Maybe you should go and see her.

28:57.560 --> 28:59.528
Maybe I should.

28:59.680 --> 29:02.763
Maybe you should go to Bizana
and talk to your father.

29:04.920 --> 29:06.809
Maybe I should.

29:09.120 --> 29:11.566
Was that a proposal?

29:13.200 --> 29:15.123
If that's what you'd like.

29:17.880 --> 29:19.689
Is it what you'd like?

29:19.840 --> 29:22.411
More than anything in the world.

29:22.560 --> 29:24.289
[CHUCKLING]

29:33.320 --> 29:35.766
- Is that "yes"?
- Yes.

29:35.960 --> 29:37.769
[LAUGHTER]

29:43.040 --> 29:45.407
[BOYS LAUGHING,
SPEAKING IN AFRICAN LANGUAGE]

29:50.040 --> 29:52.884
[WOMEN SINGING IN AFRICAN LANGUAGE]

29:53.040 --> 29:55.930
[SINGING CONTINUES]

30:06.760 --> 30:09.206
[SINGING CONTINUES]

30:22.040 --> 30:24.281
[SPEAKING IN AFRICAN LANGUAGE]

30:33.600 --> 30:34.965
Your husband.

30:46.120 --> 30:49.567
[WEDDING PARTY SINGING AT A DISTANCE]

30:56.600 --> 30:59.251
[SINGING CONTINUES]

31:13.520 --> 31:17.161
[SINGING FADES]

31:23.120 --> 31:24.565
[LAUGHING]

31:33.600 --> 31:36.649
<i>[REPORTER] At Sharpeville, an industrial
township, thousands gather outside</i>

31:36.800 --> 31:39.883
<i>a police station in protest
against new laws requiring</i>

31:40.080 --> 31:42.560
<i>every African to carry
a pass at all times.</i>

31:42.720 --> 31:44.643
[CHEERING]

31:48.480 --> 31:50.528
[POLICEMAN] The bastards
ignored the planes, man.

31:50.720 --> 31:53.200
No, no, they weren't scared at all.
They bloody well waved at me...

31:53.360 --> 31:56.364
- [SPEAKING AFRIKAANS]
- They're tearing the fences apart.

31:56.560 --> 31:58.324
[DEMONSTRATORS SHOUTING]

31:59.280 --> 32:01.248
- Listen, I'm trying...
- [RINGING]

32:02.680 --> 32:04.091
[MAN] The cells are full.

32:04.240 --> 32:05.730
[MAN 2] How long is it gonna take?

32:05.880 --> 32:08.531
- [CROWD SHOUTING]
- [OFFICER SPEAKS AFRIKAANS]

32:19.040 --> 32:21.327
- Back.
- Get away.

32:23.720 --> 32:25.609
Pienaar!

32:28.400 --> 32:30.641
[SHOUTING IN AFRIKAANS]

32:34.080 --> 32:36.606
[SHOUTING IN AFRIKAANS]

32:36.760 --> 32:39.286
Disperse and go back
to the stadium!

32:39.440 --> 32:41.488
This is your final warning!

32:41.640 --> 32:43.324
[SHOUTS]

32:45.080 --> 32:46.570
[SHOOTING CONTINUES]

32:46.720 --> 32:48.609
[SCREAMING]

32:54.680 --> 32:56.762
[SHOUTING AND GUNFIRE]

33:05.400 --> 33:06.731
Cease fire!

33:11.320 --> 33:14.688
Did you find a gun?
You'd better find that gun, Pienaar.

33:14.840 --> 33:17.889
Did you see a weapon?
You find that weapon, Pienaar.

33:18.040 --> 33:21.010
<i>[REPORTER] Between 50 and 100
were killed and hundreds injured.</i>

33:21.160 --> 33:23.481
<i>[REPORTER 2] ...police killed 69
Africans in the township of...</i>

33:23.640 --> 33:25.608
<i>[REPORTER 3] ...most of the victims
were shot in the back.</i>

33:25.760 --> 33:27.967
<i>[REPORTER 4] ...men, women, and children
were killed or wounded.</i>

33:28.120 --> 33:30.248
<i>[REPORTER 5] ...tragic consequence
of the desperate endeavor</i>

33:30.440 --> 33:32.010
<i>to preserve white supremacy.</i>

33:32.160 --> 33:35.000
<i>[REPORTER 6] ...reacted hysterically
to an event that stunned the world.</i>

33:45.760 --> 33:50.129
<i>[MANDELA] We no longer accept
the authority of a state</i>

33:50.280 --> 33:52.487
<i>that makes war on its own people.</i>

34:13.719 --> 34:16.007
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]

34:23.199 --> 34:26.601
Oliver has gone abroad
to run the movement in exile.

34:29.000 --> 34:30.650
I'm going underground.

34:34.320 --> 34:36.288
[SIGHS]

34:36.440 --> 34:41.206
The movement has
always been nonviolent.

34:41.360 --> 34:43.168
Nonviolent.

34:45.320 --> 34:46.731
Not anymore.

35:15.120 --> 35:17.600
[CAR ENGINE RUNNING]

35:29.200 --> 35:30.565
[COCKS GUN]

36:07.160 --> 36:09.845
<i>- [MAN, ON SCREEN] How's Miriam?
- [MAN 2] She's fine.</i>

36:10.000 --> 36:11.331
<i>[MAN] Well, that's fine, fine.</i>

36:14.480 --> 36:16.767
[AUDIENCE MURMURING]

36:21.320 --> 36:25.564
She is good-looking, but you must
give me Sophia Loren any day.

36:25.720 --> 36:27.609
[LAUGHTER]

36:27.760 --> 36:30.127
- [SHOUTING IN AFRICAN LANGUAGE]
- Amandla!

36:30.280 --> 36:33.329
- Spear of the Nation.
- [ALL] Yes!

36:33.480 --> 36:37.007
- We are the people of this nation.
- [ALL] Yes.

36:37.160 --> 36:40.209
- But we don't have power.
- [ALL] Yes.

36:40.360 --> 36:41.566
We don't have rights, then.

36:41.760 --> 36:43.364
- [ALL] Yes.
- We don't have justice.

36:43.520 --> 36:44.442
[ALL] Yes.

36:44.600 --> 36:47.251
South Africa now is
a land ruled by the gun.

36:47.400 --> 36:49.209
[ALL] Yes.

36:49.360 --> 36:53.809
There comes a time
in the life of every nation

36:53.960 --> 36:56.691
when there remains two choices.

36:56.840 --> 36:58.205
Submit...

36:58.400 --> 37:00.402
- [ALL SHOUTING]
- Never! Never!

37:01.600 --> 37:04.080
- ...or fight!
- [CHEERING]

37:05.480 --> 37:08.404
- We must fight.
- [CHEERING]

37:08.560 --> 37:11.723
[ALL CHANTING]
Fight! Fight! Fight! Fight!

37:11.880 --> 37:16.727
Fight! Fight! Fight! Fight!
Fight! Fight! Fight!

37:17.920 --> 37:18.842
[BABY CRYING]

37:19.000 --> 37:22.607
Don't worry, we'll find him
and then we'll hang him.

37:22.800 --> 37:26.407
Then you'll need a new man
to keep you warm at night, won't you?

37:38.760 --> 37:41.127
Amos, this is David.

37:41.760 --> 37:43.728
Can you take him
to the domestic quarters?

37:43.880 --> 37:45.723
Yeah, boss.

37:45.880 --> 37:47.041
Good morning, tata.

37:55.880 --> 37:58.531
[MAN]
Inner tube of a ballpoint pen.

37:58.680 --> 38:00.887
The thicker the plug,
the more time you've got.

38:01.640 --> 38:04.530
Aluminum powder mixed
with permanganate of potash.

38:04.680 --> 38:07.286
You can get this for
washing lettuce.

38:08.920 --> 38:12.447
When the acid reaches
the mixture, it catalyzes...

38:13.840 --> 38:15.683
and you've got...
[IMITATES EXPLOSION]

38:20.120 --> 38:21.281
[GRUNTS]

38:24.840 --> 38:26.763
[CAR ENGINE ACCELERATES]

38:29.680 --> 38:31.125
[TIRES SCREECHING]

38:34.040 --> 38:35.530
[POWERING DOWN]

38:43.920 --> 38:47.208
Kathy, it's Nelson.

38:47.360 --> 38:49.522
<i>They're calling me a terrorist.</i>

38:49.720 --> 38:51.927
<i>I need to set the record straight.</i>

38:52.080 --> 38:54.651
<i>Now, find a foreign journalist.</i>

38:54.800 --> 38:55.722
Let's go.

38:55.880 --> 38:57.882
<i>[MANDELA] I want the world to know.</i>

38:58.040 --> 39:02.045
OK, I've been accused of running away
and not standing up for my beliefs.

39:02.200 --> 39:05.602
Now, tell them
that I will not give myself up

39:05.760 --> 39:08.161
to a government I do not recognize.

39:08.360 --> 39:11.762
<i>We have been forced
into an armed struggle.</i>

39:11.920 --> 39:17.723
<i>The decision was not taken lightly
by myself or the people or the ANC.</i>

39:24.520 --> 39:25.920
<i>[REPORTER] Brian Widlake, ITN News.</i>

39:27.840 --> 39:30.605
I have a few questions for you.
Mr. Mandela,

39:30.800 --> 39:32.325
if the government doesn't
give in to the concessions

39:32.480 --> 39:37.202
- that you want, will there be violence?
- There is violence now.

39:37.360 --> 39:41.046
For 50 years, we have been
talking peace and nonviolence.

39:41.200 --> 39:44.761
The government's reply is violence,
armed attacks

39:44.920 --> 39:47.730
on unarmed and defenseless people.

39:47.880 --> 39:50.326
If you were us, what would you do?

39:50.480 --> 39:54.201
Mr. Mandela, what is it
that you personally want?

39:54.360 --> 39:56.010
I want freedom.

39:56.200 --> 40:01.161
<i>I have beautiful children,
a beautiful wife.</i>

40:01.320 --> 40:03.800
<i>I want them to walk free
in their own land.</i>

40:06.520 --> 40:08.807
Madiba, we must go.

40:16.840 --> 40:19.889
- Hey, it's Daddy.
- [CHUCKLES]

40:20.560 --> 40:22.483
Hey!
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey,

40:22.640 --> 40:25.086
hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

40:25.240 --> 40:26.651
Look at you, look at you.

40:29.280 --> 40:32.409
- It's OK.
- Oh, it's Daddy.

40:32.560 --> 40:33.971
[GIRL SQUEALING]

40:34.160 --> 40:37.209
- Look, it's Daddy.
- [LAUGHTER]

40:37.840 --> 40:41.162
- Are you smiling for Daddy?
- Do you want to come run with Dad?

40:41.320 --> 40:44.449
Come, come, let's go.
Come. Come, Zeni.

40:47.880 --> 40:50.850
- How are you?
- I'm fine.

40:51.000 --> 40:53.162
I've lost the new job, though.

40:54.080 --> 40:58.483
- I will see that you get some help.
- No. I'll be all right.

40:59.640 --> 41:01.529
I knew how it would be.

41:03.920 --> 41:06.400
Fight them.

41:06.560 --> 41:08.642
I hate them so much.

41:21.760 --> 41:22.841
[CLATTERING]

41:38.280 --> 41:40.203
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

41:40.360 --> 41:42.203
[KATHY] Petrus didn't make it.

41:44.200 --> 41:45.964
What happened?

41:46.120 --> 41:48.327
The detonator went off too soon.

41:49.400 --> 41:51.448
I'm so sorry, Madiba.

41:51.600 --> 41:53.568
It's not safe here anymore.

41:53.720 --> 41:55.449
Time for you to move on.

42:27.640 --> 42:29.449
You are at the wrong place.

42:29.600 --> 42:30.647
Police!

42:31.920 --> 42:32.921
Go, go, go!

42:33.080 --> 42:35.242
- Run, run!
- You two take the outbuildings

42:35.400 --> 42:37.080
- and we'll take the farm.
- [DOGS BARKING]

42:37.120 --> 42:38.724
Get down on the floor!

42:40.040 --> 42:42.008
Get in there!
Get in there!

42:42.200 --> 42:43.964
- Search them!
- Come here!

42:44.160 --> 42:46.845
- Get down on the floor!
- Come on!

42:47.040 --> 42:49.202
Watch out, there's one
going out the back.

42:49.360 --> 42:50.691
Take him down!
Take him down!

42:50.880 --> 42:52.086
Keep still!

42:53.640 --> 42:55.244
[TIRES SQUEALING]

42:58.600 --> 43:00.011
[SHOUTING]

43:02.040 --> 43:05.010
[SHOUTING]

43:05.880 --> 43:06.881
Don't move!

43:10.440 --> 43:12.249
[TIRES SQUEALING]

43:17.320 --> 43:19.243
[GUNS COCKING]

43:27.000 --> 43:29.651
Does somebody want me?

43:36.920 --> 43:38.445
[HANDCUFFS CLICKING]

43:38.600 --> 43:41.171
- [DOGS BARKING]
- [PANTING]

43:44.600 --> 43:47.001
[PANTING]

43:50.800 --> 43:52.325
[HORN HONKS]

43:54.680 --> 43:56.842
Mama Winnie! Mama Winnie!

43:59.720 --> 44:02.690
- They caught him.
- [GASPS]

44:09.920 --> 44:11.490
[ALL CHANTING] Mandela!

44:11.640 --> 44:15.690
Mandela!

44:15.880 --> 44:18.850
Sisulu!

44:19.760 --> 44:21.489
Kathrada!

44:21.640 --> 44:23.449
[CHANTING CONTINUES]

44:29.640 --> 44:31.529
No children.
You can't take them in.

44:31.680 --> 44:33.091
Don't touch me.

44:33.240 --> 44:35.641
- [SPEAKING AFRIKAANS]
- Don't touch me.

44:42.840 --> 44:45.844
Mama will come back, OK?
All right?

44:47.320 --> 44:51.803
- Now, wait with sisi, OK?
- [CHANTING CONTINUES]

44:58.240 --> 44:59.287
[CROWD] Mandela!

45:00.000 --> 45:04.050
Mandela! Mandela!

45:17.360 --> 45:21.490
[CROWD MURMURING]

45:23.280 --> 45:24.930
[MURMURING QUIETS]

45:25.080 --> 45:27.731
[CROWD WHISPERING]

45:34.400 --> 45:37.404
[SHOUTING IN AFRICAN LANGUAGE]

45:39.920 --> 45:41.570
- [MAN] Silence!
- [CHANTING CONTINUES]

45:41.720 --> 45:43.609
- [GAVEL POUNDING]
- Silence!

45:43.800 --> 45:45.450
[CROWD MURMURING]

45:48.960 --> 45:51.042
Quiet! Quiet!

46:01.560 --> 46:05.326
My Lord, I call the case of the state
against the national high command

46:05.480 --> 46:09.610
of Umkhonto we Sizwe, the military wing
of the African National Congress.

46:10.800 --> 46:14.850
The state contends that the accused
are responsible for acts of sabotage

46:15.040 --> 46:19.682
aimed at facilitating violent revolution
and an armed invasion of this country

46:19.880 --> 46:23.327
with the intention
of overthrowing the government.

46:25.960 --> 46:28.964
Accused number one, Nelson Mandela.

46:29.120 --> 46:32.169
Do you plead guilty or not guilty?

46:32.320 --> 46:34.561
My Lord, it is not I

46:34.720 --> 46:37.803
but the government
that should be put in the dock.

46:37.960 --> 46:40.440
- [CROWD MURMURING]
- I plead not guilty.

46:40.600 --> 46:42.523
[CROWD GASPING]

46:43.560 --> 46:46.723
The state has formally advised me

46:46.880 --> 46:49.531
that they will be asking
for the supreme penalty

46:49.680 --> 46:51.682
permissible by law.

46:52.880 --> 46:54.564
Which is death.

46:55.840 --> 46:59.083
Our best chance is to attack
the credibility of the charges.

46:59.240 --> 47:02.642
We dispute every falsehood,
we challenge every charge.

47:04.840 --> 47:06.683
We think they'll bring
in a guilty verdict,

47:06.880 --> 47:09.884
but we might be able to
avoid the death sentence.

47:14.040 --> 47:16.520
- Agreed?
- Agreed.

47:16.680 --> 47:18.045
[MUTTERING] Agreed.

47:19.040 --> 47:20.849
Then be happy.

47:21.000 --> 47:22.889
Smile.

47:23.040 --> 47:27.125
This may be the greatest service
we will ever do for our people.

47:27.320 --> 47:30.403
[CROWD CHANTING OUTSIDE]

47:30.560 --> 47:33.723
[CHANTING] Mandela! Mandela!

47:48.200 --> 47:50.487
My name is Nelson Mandela.

47:50.680 --> 47:52.330
I'm the first accused.

47:54.480 --> 47:59.247
I do not deny that
I planned sabotage.

47:59.400 --> 48:02.051
I did not plan it

48:02.200 --> 48:04.487
in a spirit of recklessness

48:04.640 --> 48:08.008
nor because I have any love
for violence.

48:08.960 --> 48:13.648
The hard facts are
that 50 years of non-violence

48:13.800 --> 48:16.326
had brought the African
people nothing

48:16.480 --> 48:20.166
but more and more
repressive legislation

48:20.320 --> 48:22.721
and fewer and fewer rights.

48:24.120 --> 48:26.441
Africans want

48:26.600 --> 48:29.843
a just share
in the whole of South Africa.

48:30.000 --> 48:32.731
We want equal political rights,

48:32.880 --> 48:35.804
one man, one vote.

48:35.960 --> 48:39.931
I have dedicated myself to this struggle
of the African people.

48:40.080 --> 48:44.290
I have fought against
white domination.

48:44.480 --> 48:47.563
I have fought against
black domination.

48:48.440 --> 48:51.364
I have cherished the
ideal of a free,

48:51.520 --> 48:54.000
democratic society
where all persons

48:54.200 --> 48:58.171
live together in harmony
with equal opportunities.

48:58.920 --> 49:02.811
It is an ideal which
I hope to live for

49:03.000 --> 49:04.650
and achieve,

49:04.800 --> 49:08.521
but, if needs be,

49:08.680 --> 49:10.921
it is an ideal for which

49:11.080 --> 49:14.368
I am prepared to die.

49:18.040 --> 49:20.964
[CROWD CHANTING]

49:22.720 --> 49:26.202
<i>- Amandla!
- Awethu!</i>

49:26.800 --> 49:30.566
<i>- Amandla!
- Awethu!</i>

49:30.720 --> 49:32.563
[CHANTING CONTINUES]

49:55.600 --> 49:58.365
Before the judge imposes
the supreme penalty,

49:58.520 --> 50:00.887
there is one more step.

50:01.040 --> 50:05.409
He will ask the first accused, Nelson,
"Have you any reason to advance

50:05.600 --> 50:07.568
whether the sentence
should not be passed?"

50:07.720 --> 50:10.769
- You could then say...
- I have nothing more to say.

50:10.920 --> 50:12.649
That won't help your appeal.

50:14.840 --> 50:16.842
There will be no appeal.

50:17.880 --> 50:19.211
No appeal?

50:19.360 --> 50:22.011
We have talked about this.
We are ready.

50:25.080 --> 50:26.605
<i>[MAN] All rise.</i>

50:39.560 --> 50:41.608
I have reached my verdict.

50:42.160 --> 50:44.162
The defendants will rise.

50:47.720 --> 50:51.042
The accused are all found
guilty as charged.

50:51.200 --> 50:53.043
[CROWD GASPING]

50:54.640 --> 50:58.486
The accused have made high moral claims
for their actions.

50:58.640 --> 51:02.122
In essence,
they have courted martyrdom

51:02.280 --> 51:05.682
at the hands of what they
call "their oppressors."

51:05.840 --> 51:11.131
But I will not give them
that satisfaction.

51:11.280 --> 51:12.486
Let us show the world

51:12.640 --> 51:16.201
that we are a nation of laws

51:16.360 --> 51:17.521
and where possible,

51:17.720 --> 51:20.803
we temper justice with mercy.

51:20.960 --> 51:25.841
I have therefore decided
not to impose the supreme penalty.

51:26.000 --> 51:28.162
[CROWD GASPING]

51:29.800 --> 51:33.964
The sentence in the case
of all the accused...

51:35.120 --> 51:37.122
will be life imprisonment.

51:39.880 --> 51:42.565
[CHANTING]

51:57.160 --> 51:59.481
[CHANTING CONTINUES]

52:25.840 --> 52:29.049
[CROWD SINGING]

53:10.560 --> 53:12.005
[BRAKES SQUEAK]

53:22.040 --> 53:23.929
[SPEAKING AFRIKAANS]

53:24.080 --> 53:25.520
[GUARD] All right, get out, kaffirs.

53:26.840 --> 53:28.330
- In a line.
- All right.

53:29.440 --> 53:32.330
- Move, move, get over there.
- Now stand in a line.

53:33.320 --> 53:34.287
All right, listen to us.

53:34.480 --> 53:35.561
- Get over there.
- Move.

53:35.720 --> 53:37.165
Form a line, go on.

53:38.680 --> 53:41.001
You're not in Johannesburg anymore.

53:41.160 --> 53:45.529
You're not in Pretoria.
You are on the island.

53:45.680 --> 53:47.682
You will never leave here again.

53:48.800 --> 53:51.690
You will never touch
a woman or a child again.

53:51.840 --> 53:53.842
You will die here.

53:54.880 --> 53:56.848
If you have any complaints,

53:57.040 --> 53:58.485
well, that's just too bad

53:58.640 --> 54:01.211
because nobody on
the island gives a shit,

54:01.360 --> 54:05.365
and nobody in the rest
of the universe will ever know.

54:05.960 --> 54:08.247
It's a pity they didn't hang you.

54:09.240 --> 54:11.607
I'm going to make sure
you wish they had.

54:14.040 --> 54:15.041
Move!

54:15.200 --> 54:17.123
[GUARDS SHOUTING IN AFRIKAANS]

54:19.560 --> 54:22.211
[SHOUTING CONTINUES]

54:26.320 --> 54:28.971
Indians get trousers.
Indians get socks.

54:30.240 --> 54:31.685
Boys get shorts.

54:32.800 --> 54:34.165
Sit down, sit down, man!

54:39.120 --> 54:41.964
Well, Kathy, it looks like
you will have to be the daddy.

54:44.120 --> 54:45.360
Move! Move, move, move!

54:45.520 --> 54:47.727
Come, put all your
civvies here in the box.

54:48.480 --> 54:49.481
Move it!

54:52.440 --> 54:54.647
I'm watching you, my friend.
Move it!

54:56.200 --> 54:57.565
Go on, go on! Move!

54:57.720 --> 54:58.960
Move!

55:02.600 --> 55:04.170
[SERGEANT] Motsoaledi.

55:04.360 --> 55:05.407
[GUARD] Motsoaledi.

55:05.560 --> 55:06.721
[SHOUTING IN AFRIKAANS]

55:06.880 --> 55:08.803
[JAIL DOOR CLOSING]

55:08.960 --> 55:10.883
- Kathrada.
- Kathrada!

55:12.240 --> 55:13.924
Kathrada, move!

55:14.960 --> 55:16.246
In!
Move, coolie!

55:16.400 --> 55:18.607
- Sisulu?
- Sisulu!

55:18.760 --> 55:20.922
Forward, come!
Move, move, move!

55:25.000 --> 55:26.889
- Mandela.
- Mandela.

55:34.760 --> 55:35.966
Go!

55:38.400 --> 55:40.880
[DOOR THUDS, LATCH CLANKS]

55:43.160 --> 55:45.367
This is it, boy... home,

55:45.520 --> 55:47.363
for the rest of your life.

55:47.520 --> 55:49.090
Mlangeni, come, move.

55:51.520 --> 55:52.681
- Mlangeni.
- Move.

55:52.840 --> 55:55.605
- Mlangeni...
- [SIGHS]

55:56.200 --> 55:58.646
[DISTANT SHOUTING]

56:09.880 --> 56:11.882
<i>Amandla!</i>

57:08.760 --> 57:10.285
[MEN SPEAKING AFRIKAANS]

57:10.440 --> 57:13.967
- Routine check.
- Get out!

57:14.120 --> 57:15.690
Stay where you are!

57:16.480 --> 57:20.326
Get out of my bedroom!
Get out!

57:20.480 --> 57:21.845
- [SHOUTING, SCREAMING]
- Hey, hey, hey.

57:22.040 --> 57:25.931
Get out! Get out!
Get out!

57:26.080 --> 57:27.684
- Get out!
- Jesus, what a witch.

57:27.880 --> 57:31.521
[PANTING]

57:36.040 --> 57:38.361
[GRUNTING]

57:46.240 --> 57:48.766
[PANTING CONTINUES]

58:04.280 --> 58:05.566
[HEAVY SIGH]

58:19.920 --> 58:21.684
[SIGHS]

58:21.840 --> 58:23.922
[GUARDS SHOUTING AND CLAPPING]

58:24.080 --> 58:26.526
Get up, you lazy kaffirs!
Time for work!

58:26.680 --> 58:30.526
- Up, Kaffir!
- [INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

58:33.600 --> 58:35.489
Come, come, come! Move!

58:35.640 --> 58:37.642
[MAN] Every morning
I've got to smell your crap.

58:37.800 --> 58:39.006
Come. Move!

58:39.200 --> 58:40.725
Get back into line, man!

58:40.880 --> 58:44.327
Listen, we are going
to start making demands,

58:44.480 --> 58:49.202
and our first demand
is going to be long trousers.

58:50.440 --> 58:53.728
We have to make them
respect us, and they will,

58:53.920 --> 58:55.604
but it will take time,

58:55.800 --> 58:59.407
but we have time,
so we start small.

58:59.560 --> 59:01.449
[SHOVEL CLANKING]

59:09.560 --> 59:12.291
[GUARDS SHOUTING IN AFRIKAANS]

59:13.760 --> 59:16.650
- Faster, faster!
- Move, move, you bloody Kaffir!

59:18.400 --> 59:19.686
Move, move!

59:25.520 --> 59:27.329
[SHOUTING CONTINUES]

59:27.480 --> 59:28.527
Lazy boy.

59:28.680 --> 59:30.808
Work. Don't stop.
You work.

59:33.360 --> 59:35.328
I heard about your wife, boy.

59:35.480 --> 59:38.324
Crazy woman.
Bitch.

59:38.480 --> 59:40.369
- Winnie...
- Hey, hey, hey!

59:40.520 --> 59:43.000
- Hey, we are not fighting.
- Just do it, boy.

59:43.160 --> 59:44.889
- Please do it.
- Madiba.

59:45.040 --> 59:48.203
- What is the problem here?
- No problem.

59:48.360 --> 59:51.091
No problem, Sergeant.
No problem.

59:51.240 --> 59:52.685
[MAN] Let's work, boys.

59:52.840 --> 59:55.605
Let's go, go, go.
Move, move, move.

59:56.480 --> 59:58.960
Every time they make us angry,
it's like they win.

01:00:00.280 --> 01:00:02.931
Never let them see you
lose your temper, Madiba.

01:00:03.120 --> 01:00:04.565
- Never.
- [MAN] Hey, what are you looking at?

01:00:04.720 --> 01:00:05.801
Turn 'round!

01:00:06.840 --> 01:00:08.763
[SPEAKING AFRIKAANS]

01:00:10.680 --> 01:00:12.205
[SPEAKING AFRICAN LANGUAGE]

01:00:12.360 --> 01:00:14.442
[GROUP CHANTING]

01:00:41.960 --> 01:00:44.645
[DISTANT CHANTING]

01:00:50.920 --> 01:00:53.685
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

01:01:09.320 --> 01:01:10.321
[WHISTLES]

01:01:14.720 --> 01:01:17.121
[DISTANT SHOUTING]

01:01:20.280 --> 01:01:21.930
[INHALES]

01:01:30.840 --> 01:01:32.444
[KICKS CELL DOOR]

01:01:36.760 --> 01:01:40.162
- Number.
- 31159.

01:01:41.520 --> 01:01:42.681
[MUTTERS]

01:01:46.720 --> 01:01:49.963
- Number.
- 46664.

01:01:50.960 --> 01:01:53.281
That is category D.

01:01:53.480 --> 01:01:55.881
That's your allocation
for the next six months.

01:02:02.640 --> 01:02:04.483
Number.

01:02:04.640 --> 01:02:07.211
[LOW, INDISTINCT TALKING IN DISTANCE]

01:02:13.040 --> 01:02:15.122
[FOOTSTEPS ECHOING]

01:02:21.000 --> 01:02:22.411
[SIGHS]

01:02:25.240 --> 01:02:27.129
[SIGHS]

01:02:45.400 --> 01:02:47.448
[SIGHING]

01:03:09.480 --> 01:03:11.608
[INAUDIBLE]

01:03:22.520 --> 01:03:24.568
[SHOUTING IN AFRIKAANS]

01:03:26.200 --> 01:03:27.690
Get these bloody dogs out of here.

01:03:27.840 --> 01:03:29.604
[SHOUTING CONTINUES]

01:03:30.600 --> 01:03:32.682
- Get out of here.
- Get in the yard, you...

01:03:32.840 --> 01:03:34.251
You, you, move it!

01:03:34.400 --> 01:03:36.368
Yes, that's it, boys.
That's good, good.

01:03:36.520 --> 01:03:37.806
In the rain, right.

01:03:38.000 --> 01:03:39.240
- Get your clothes off.
- Strip!

01:03:39.280 --> 01:03:43.490
- Take your clothes off.
- Strip! Strip! Strip!

01:03:43.640 --> 01:03:45.130
Fucking strip!

01:03:45.280 --> 01:03:47.203
- Strip!
- You stink!

01:03:47.360 --> 01:03:50.682
- Let's wash the stink off you!
- You are nothing!

01:03:52.240 --> 01:03:54.925
- [MEN CONTINUE SHOUTING]
- [CLATTERING]

01:03:57.880 --> 01:03:59.325
[SERGEANT] When they think
of you in the morning,

01:03:59.520 --> 01:04:01.329
they'll think they're
gonna shit themselves!

01:04:02.000 --> 01:04:04.765
Night in the rain, huh?
Useless kaffirs.

01:04:04.920 --> 01:04:06.445
You understand, boys?

01:04:06.600 --> 01:04:08.602
You're going to stand
here all night!

01:04:08.760 --> 01:04:09.807
You monkeys!

01:04:09.960 --> 01:04:12.327
You don't wear clothes
up in your trees, do you?

01:04:12.480 --> 01:04:14.050
You black baboon kaffirs!

01:04:14.240 --> 01:04:16.368
Stand still in the line.
Useless kaffirs.

01:04:16.520 --> 01:04:18.249
- Stand up.
- Get up, up, up!

01:04:18.400 --> 01:04:21.131
Stand up! Stand up, you slacker!

01:04:21.280 --> 01:04:23.647
You tell your commanding
officer I will be complaining

01:04:23.800 --> 01:04:25.882
to the head of the prison
service in Pretoria.

01:04:26.040 --> 01:04:28.168
You tell him that!

01:04:28.320 --> 01:04:30.766
- [DISTANT SHOUTING]
- [THUNDER RUMBLING]

01:04:33.240 --> 01:04:35.163
[THUNDER RUMBLING ECHOING]

01:04:47.600 --> 01:04:50.490
[DRIPPING]

01:04:52.720 --> 01:04:55.246
[DISTANT SCREAMING]

01:04:57.840 --> 01:05:00.002
[SCREAMING CONTINUES]

01:05:03.360 --> 01:05:05.249
Get up.

01:05:10.000 --> 01:05:12.401
You've got a complaint
to make to Pretoria?

01:05:12.560 --> 01:05:13.607
Yes, Colonel.

01:05:14.800 --> 01:05:18.168
This prison is out of control,
and those prison guards are nothing

01:05:18.320 --> 01:05:20.288
but some drunk hooligans.

01:05:20.440 --> 01:05:23.569
What right do they
have to assault us?

01:05:23.720 --> 01:05:29.170
Now, are you part of a justice system
or gangsters in uniform?

01:05:29.360 --> 01:05:32.011
You think you can scare me
with this shit about Pretoria?

01:05:32.160 --> 01:05:34.049
If those idiots don't
like what I do,

01:05:34.240 --> 01:05:37.562
they can sack me.
I don't need their job.

01:05:37.720 --> 01:05:39.722
My family's got five farms.

01:05:39.880 --> 01:05:42.406
I've got money. I do what I like.

01:05:46.920 --> 01:05:49.685
Have you got anything
else to say to me?

01:05:49.880 --> 01:05:51.769
Yes.

01:05:51.920 --> 01:05:55.049
I've put in a request
for long trousers.

01:05:55.200 --> 01:05:57.441
Long trousers.

01:06:00.280 --> 01:06:02.044
He wants long trousers.

01:06:05.200 --> 01:06:07.885
[CHANTING]

01:06:10.440 --> 01:06:12.761
Mandela, follow me.

01:06:12.920 --> 01:06:14.922
[CHANTING CONTINUES]

01:06:23.880 --> 01:06:27.248
Speak English only.
Family matters only.

01:06:27.400 --> 01:06:31.041
Any political talk,
and I'll terminate the visit. Sit.

01:06:40.520 --> 01:06:41.851
[SIGHS]

01:06:42.760 --> 01:06:44.728
Are you all right?

01:06:45.760 --> 01:06:48.684
Yes, I'm all right.

01:06:48.840 --> 01:06:50.888
Tell me about you.

01:06:52.440 --> 01:06:54.727
I'm under a banning order.

01:06:56.760 --> 01:06:58.524
But don't worry.

01:06:59.680 --> 01:07:01.444
Our friends are helping me.

01:07:04.960 --> 01:07:06.962
The girls send their love.

01:07:08.200 --> 01:07:10.282
They want to see you.

01:07:10.440 --> 01:07:12.204
I think of them every day.

01:07:13.600 --> 01:07:14.522
[SIGHS]

01:07:14.680 --> 01:07:16.648
You must tell them I love them.

01:07:18.800 --> 01:07:22.009
They're not allowed visits
until they're 16.

01:07:24.560 --> 01:07:26.722
Zindzi's not yet five.

01:07:29.560 --> 01:07:33.690
- Tell me about the arrests.
- [SIGHS]

01:07:34.720 --> 01:07:37.610
It's nothing I can't deal with.

01:07:37.760 --> 01:07:41.731
They like to have
little chats with me.

01:07:43.240 --> 01:07:46.449
Usually they wait till just before
the girls come back from school

01:07:46.600 --> 01:07:48.125
to take me away.

01:07:50.200 --> 01:07:52.407
So the girls will
find an empty home.

01:07:55.880 --> 01:07:58.724
They think about these things,
you know.

01:08:00.560 --> 01:08:03.848
They think about me a lot.

01:08:09.120 --> 01:08:12.727
- How do you bear it?
- By hating them.

01:08:12.880 --> 01:08:15.121
And don't tell me I'm wrong,
it keeps me strong.

01:08:15.320 --> 01:08:17.926
Hey. Family matters only.

01:08:19.439 --> 01:08:22.171
Your mother, Madiba,

01:08:22.319 --> 01:08:24.209
she is sick.

01:08:26.000 --> 01:08:28.127
They say she will die soon.

01:08:36.720 --> 01:08:38.529
I have failed her.

01:08:38.680 --> 01:08:40.045
No.

01:08:41.399 --> 01:08:43.368
She understands.

01:08:44.640 --> 01:08:46.210
And she's proud of you.

01:08:47.200 --> 01:08:49.202
Is that true?

01:08:49.359 --> 01:08:51.600
She told me so herself.

01:09:01.800 --> 01:09:03.564
Mandela, let's go.

01:09:34.560 --> 01:09:36.483
Don't touch my children!

01:09:36.640 --> 01:09:38.483
- Do not touch my children!
- Get in there!

01:09:38.640 --> 01:09:41.291
- Do not... touch my children!
- [CHILD] Mama!

01:09:41.439 --> 01:09:43.680
Don't you ever touch my children!

01:09:43.840 --> 01:09:46.207
- Mama!
- Mama!

01:09:46.359 --> 01:09:48.840
Mummy will come back.
Stay in the house.

01:09:49.000 --> 01:09:50.604
Mummy will come back.
Stay in...

01:09:50.760 --> 01:09:55.561
- In, Kaffir.
- [ZINDZI] Mama! Mama!

01:09:55.720 --> 01:09:58.041
[ENGINE STARTS, WINNIE GASPING]

01:09:58.200 --> 01:09:59.884
Mama!

01:10:01.520 --> 01:10:05.320
- Mama?
- [SOBBING] Mama!

01:10:05.480 --> 01:10:07.084
[DOGS BARKING IN DISTANCE]

01:10:08.520 --> 01:10:09.931
<i>[WINNIE] Where are my children?!</i>

01:10:10.360 --> 01:10:12.567
Where are my children?

01:10:12.720 --> 01:10:14.085
Where are my children?!

01:10:14.240 --> 01:10:17.926
What have you done to my children?!
Where are my children?!

01:10:18.080 --> 01:10:19.764
Where are my children?

01:10:19.920 --> 01:10:22.810
Where are my... children?!

01:10:33.200 --> 01:10:36.090
<i>[MANDELA] My darling daughters.</i>

01:10:36.240 --> 01:10:39.926
<i>I have been told that
our beloved mama</i>

01:10:40.080 --> 01:10:42.401
has been arrested again.

01:10:44.120 --> 01:10:45.849
<i>This is hard for me</i>

01:10:46.000 --> 01:10:49.766
<i>because I am the source
of all your troubles.</i>

01:10:49.920 --> 01:10:52.287
[GUARD] Mandela, move!

01:10:54.640 --> 01:10:57.564
<i>All that I wish for you
to bear in mind</i>

01:10:57.720 --> 01:11:01.691
<i>is that we have a brave
and determined mother</i>

01:11:01.840 --> 01:11:06.050
<i>who loves her people
with all of her heart.</i>

01:11:06.960 --> 01:11:08.325
<i>When you are grown up,</i>

01:11:08.480 --> 01:11:12.644
<i>you will understand how she
has sacrificed her own happiness</i>

01:11:12.800 --> 01:11:16.327
<i>in the battle for
truth and justice.</i>

01:11:21.640 --> 01:11:25.690
<i>I am only allowed
to send you two letters a year.</i>

01:11:26.360 --> 01:11:29.807
<i>I am told you have not
been getting them...</i>

01:11:31.480 --> 01:11:33.721
<i>but I shall keep on writing.</i>

01:11:33.880 --> 01:11:37.566
<i>There's so little I can do for you.</i>

01:11:39.200 --> 01:11:42.249
<i>These letters are the only means</i>

01:11:42.440 --> 01:11:46.286
<i>of passing my love to you.</i>

01:11:56.640 --> 01:11:58.165
[SIGHS]

01:12:05.600 --> 01:12:08.285
[SKITTERING]

01:12:17.760 --> 01:12:20.684
[SPEAKING AFRIKAANS]

01:12:22.960 --> 01:12:24.086
Hands up!

01:12:29.680 --> 01:12:30.761
[GASPS]

01:12:37.480 --> 01:12:39.926
- Could I...
- Louder.

01:12:42.080 --> 01:12:44.890
Go toilet.
Go to...

01:12:45.040 --> 01:12:47.361
All you have to do is help us.

01:12:47.520 --> 01:12:50.000
Then you can go back
to your children.

01:12:50.800 --> 01:12:53.531
I piss on you.

01:12:58.080 --> 01:12:59.969
Bloody black bitch!

01:13:01.120 --> 01:13:03.487
No, no!

01:13:08.360 --> 01:13:11.489
[DISTANT SHOUTING]

01:13:17.320 --> 01:13:20.767
- [SIGHS]
- [SHOUTING CONTINUES]

01:13:25.720 --> 01:13:27.882
[LAUGHTER]

01:13:58.200 --> 01:13:59.770
[GASPS]

01:14:02.040 --> 01:14:04.611
[MANDELA]
I dreamt about Winnie last night.

01:14:04.760 --> 01:14:07.081
Thembi was there, too.

01:14:07.240 --> 01:14:09.846
He's living right
there in Cape Town.

01:14:10.840 --> 01:14:14.049
Ah, maybe he'll come
and visit you one day.

01:14:14.200 --> 01:14:16.407
It's not been easy on the boy.

01:14:16.560 --> 01:14:17.641
Man, you terrorists.

01:14:17.800 --> 01:14:19.882
Most dangerous men in Africa.

01:14:20.040 --> 01:14:22.122
You're a bunch of wild animals.

01:14:23.120 --> 01:14:24.880
[GUARD] What are you looking at?
Turn around.

01:14:25.280 --> 01:14:27.931
Wild animals, the lot of you.

01:14:28.800 --> 01:14:30.450
Now I get it.
We're in a zoo.

01:14:30.600 --> 01:14:32.409
I see myself more like a lion.

01:14:34.400 --> 01:14:36.926
- A tiger.
- No tigers in Africa, Madiba.

01:14:37.080 --> 01:14:38.206
Who told you that?

01:14:38.360 --> 01:14:40.169
No, it's a fact,
there have never been tigers.

01:14:40.320 --> 01:14:43.369
- There are African tigers, Kathy.
- What kind of a lawyer is a tiger?

01:14:43.520 --> 01:14:47.491
- Lawyers are cheetahs, Madiba.
- [LAUGHTER]

01:14:47.640 --> 01:14:49.802
[GUARD] Work, you lazy buggers!

01:14:53.160 --> 01:14:54.525
[SHOUTING IN AFRIKAANS]

01:14:57.000 --> 01:14:59.970
Hurry up!
Stop shuffling, you lazy Kaffir.

01:15:02.040 --> 01:15:03.485
Hey, boy.

01:15:04.800 --> 01:15:06.643
You think you're smart, don't you?

01:15:06.800 --> 01:15:09.724
Can't be that smart,
otherwise I wouldn't be here.

01:15:10.640 --> 01:15:13.883
You're going to be on this shit island
for the rest of your life.

01:15:14.040 --> 01:15:15.530
I'll be gone in a year.

01:15:16.640 --> 01:15:18.369
Why wait so long?

01:15:19.360 --> 01:15:21.522
I mean,
your family have five farms.

01:15:21.680 --> 01:15:24.729
You've got money.
You don't need this job.

01:15:24.880 --> 01:15:28.362
- Who told you that?
- You did.

01:15:30.960 --> 01:15:32.849
[GUARDS SHOUTING]

01:15:33.000 --> 01:15:36.243
- Long trousers!
- Long trousers!

01:15:36.400 --> 01:15:38.323
[SHOUTING, LAUGHTER]

01:15:41.840 --> 01:15:45.049
- Long trousers!
- [LAUGHTER CONTINUES]

01:15:45.200 --> 01:15:47.601
[SHOUTING CONTINUES]

01:15:50.520 --> 01:15:51.851
Look at this!

01:15:56.640 --> 01:15:58.165
Long trousers.

01:15:58.680 --> 01:15:59.727
Can you believe it?

01:16:00.760 --> 01:16:03.684
Kathy, you are no longer the daddy.

01:16:04.760 --> 01:16:05.841
Well done, Madiba.

01:16:06.040 --> 01:16:08.646
[CLINKING]

01:16:20.160 --> 01:16:21.889
Telegram.

01:16:24.360 --> 01:16:25.361
Have you read it?

01:16:27.800 --> 01:16:30.167
[CLINKING CONTINUES]

01:16:53.120 --> 01:16:56.488
[STIFLED SOBBING]

01:17:06.640 --> 01:17:09.371
But he's my firstborn son.

01:17:10.360 --> 01:17:13.284
It is my duty to bury him.

01:17:13.480 --> 01:17:17.041
The orders are you're not
to leave the island, ever.

01:17:20.400 --> 01:17:23.051
I'm sorry.
That's just the way it is.

01:17:26.040 --> 01:17:27.929
<i>Tata.</i>

01:17:50.480 --> 01:17:51.720
Madiba?

01:17:55.160 --> 01:17:57.083
I'm losing them all.

01:18:01.280 --> 01:18:02.850
My mother.

01:18:04.880 --> 01:18:06.291
My son.

01:18:09.000 --> 01:18:10.411
My wife.

01:18:15.040 --> 01:18:18.886
[HEAVY SIGH]

01:18:31.840 --> 01:18:32.966
Come now.

01:18:36.600 --> 01:18:37.886
Thank you.

01:19:20.200 --> 01:19:23.170
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:19:27.240 --> 01:19:28.765
[CROWD CHANTING] Winnie! Winnie!

01:19:28.920 --> 01:19:31.002
Winnie! Winnie! Winnie!

01:19:31.200 --> 01:19:32.531
Winnie! Winnie!

01:19:32.680 --> 01:19:34.728
Winnie! Winnie! Winnie!

01:19:34.880 --> 01:19:36.370
Winnie! Winnie!

01:19:36.520 --> 01:19:37.851
Winnie! Winnie...

01:19:38.040 --> 01:19:40.805
[CHANTING CONTINUES]

01:19:46.800 --> 01:19:49.963
[CHANTING CONTINUES]

01:19:55.080 --> 01:19:56.241
Winnie?

01:19:58.360 --> 01:20:00.488
Winnie, how does it feel?

01:20:02.440 --> 01:20:03.726
We love you, Winnie!

01:20:05.480 --> 01:20:08.404
[SOBBING]

01:20:16.640 --> 01:20:17.880
Sisi.

01:20:30.640 --> 01:20:32.529
[REPORTER] Winnie, talk to us.

01:20:32.720 --> 01:20:34.404
Are you gonna make a statement?

01:20:34.600 --> 01:20:36.682
I say to my jailers...

01:20:38.080 --> 01:20:40.128
"Thank you."

01:20:40.280 --> 01:20:42.886
And I say to the government,

01:20:43.040 --> 01:20:45.281
"Thank you.

01:20:45.480 --> 01:20:48.006
You've helped me grow up."

01:20:49.000 --> 01:20:51.890
I was very young
when I married Nelson.

01:20:52.040 --> 01:20:54.725
- [MAN] Yes, yes.
- I'm not young anymore.

01:20:56.440 --> 01:21:00.331
And I am not afraid anymore.

01:21:00.480 --> 01:21:03.051
[CROWD MURMURING IN AGREEMENT]

01:21:04.160 --> 01:21:05.321
<i>Amandla!</i>

01:21:05.480 --> 01:21:07.448
<i>Awethu!</i>

01:21:08.520 --> 01:21:10.010
[WOMAN]
What are you going to do now?

01:21:10.160 --> 01:21:12.049
[CROWD CHANTING]
Winnie! Winnie! Winnie!

01:21:13.520 --> 01:21:15.010
[♪ BOB MARLEY & THE WAILERS: "WAR"]

01:21:24.400 --> 01:21:25.890
[CLANKING]

01:21:33.400 --> 01:21:36.244
[GUNSHOTS, SCREAMING]

01:21:38.240 --> 01:21:41.369
- [SCREAMING]
- [WHIRRING]

01:21:43.440 --> 01:21:45.761
[SCREAMING]

01:21:59.880 --> 01:22:01.325
[SHOUTING]

01:22:08.120 --> 01:22:10.407
[INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

01:22:12.640 --> 01:22:14.051
Move!

01:22:14.240 --> 01:22:16.447
[SHOUTING CONTINUES]

01:22:22.360 --> 01:22:24.089
Are you Nelson Mandela?

01:22:27.000 --> 01:22:28.240
Yes.

01:22:29.480 --> 01:22:31.448
[MAN] This is what you do?

01:22:33.280 --> 01:22:35.123
This is what I do.

01:22:35.280 --> 01:22:38.204
I told you these
old men had given up.

01:22:38.360 --> 01:22:40.886
- You must show respect, man.
- Respect?

01:22:41.040 --> 01:22:43.122
They're killing us on the streets.

01:22:44.120 --> 01:22:47.886
But even the children are fighting back,
and he grows tomatoes.

01:22:48.680 --> 01:22:50.091
What is your name?

01:22:50.240 --> 01:22:52.129
My name is Patrick Lekota.

01:22:53.160 --> 01:22:56.926
Mr. Lekota, we have been
in prison for a very long time.

01:22:57.080 --> 01:23:03.042
We would be very happy
to listen to you, to learn.

01:23:03.200 --> 01:23:06.443
We closed down the schools,
all the schools.

01:23:07.480 --> 01:23:09.323
[PATRICK] There was no ANC.

01:23:11.240 --> 01:23:13.163
We don't need your ANC.

01:23:16.760 --> 01:23:20.765
I can see...
that you are very brave.

01:23:20.920 --> 01:23:22.126
And you...

01:23:23.880 --> 01:23:25.166
and you.

01:23:26.520 --> 01:23:29.000
But alone, what can you do?

01:23:33.960 --> 01:23:36.088
Together we have power.

01:23:37.360 --> 01:23:38.964
Together.

01:23:40.600 --> 01:23:43.331
You and I can be killed

01:23:43.480 --> 01:23:45.767
or imprisoned,

01:23:45.920 --> 01:23:48.651
but the organization goes on...

01:23:48.800 --> 01:23:50.450
forever.

01:23:52.200 --> 01:23:53.929
[GUARDS SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

01:23:54.080 --> 01:23:56.526
- [GUARD] Go back now!
- [MAN] Aye, aye, brave man.

01:23:57.800 --> 01:23:59.484
[GUARD] You'll march with the line!

01:24:04.040 --> 01:24:05.565
[SIGHS]

01:24:34.240 --> 01:24:36.208
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

01:24:38.760 --> 01:24:40.603
[DOOR CLANKING]

01:24:46.680 --> 01:24:50.162
- [CELL DOOR SLAMS]
- [LOCK CLICKING]

01:24:50.320 --> 01:24:53.085
<i>[MANDELA] So, did Brent do well
in his examination?</i>

01:24:53.240 --> 01:24:54.730
Not too bad.

01:24:55.480 --> 01:24:57.164
What about Zane?

01:24:57.360 --> 01:24:59.567
It must be his 14th birthday soon.

01:24:59.720 --> 01:25:00.767
Just like you.

01:25:00.920 --> 01:25:03.605
Do you ever forget anything?

01:25:06.240 --> 01:25:10.131
Last time I saw Zindzi,
she wasn't even three.

01:25:13.400 --> 01:25:15.243
[DISTANT CONVERSATIONS]

01:25:17.920 --> 01:25:20.082
[SOBS QUIETLY]

01:25:22.640 --> 01:25:24.290
Zindzi.

01:25:25.560 --> 01:25:27.961
You are so beautiful.

01:25:30.040 --> 01:25:34.284
I think of you every day,
but it's the little girl that I see.

01:25:34.480 --> 01:25:37.529
And now you have grown
to be a beautiful young woman.

01:25:40.600 --> 01:25:42.090
[SOBS]

01:25:44.200 --> 01:25:47.921
- How is your mother?
- You know Mama.

01:25:48.120 --> 01:25:49.849
She's a fighter.

01:25:51.920 --> 01:25:53.251
And you?

01:25:53.400 --> 01:25:55.209
I'm your daughter.

01:25:55.360 --> 01:25:56.646
I want to fight, too.

01:25:56.800 --> 01:25:58.131
There's no politics.

01:25:58.280 --> 01:26:01.045
That is not politics,
that is my life.

01:26:04.560 --> 01:26:07.962
You have your mother's spirit.
[CHUCKLES]

01:26:08.960 --> 01:26:10.200
[CHUCKLES]

01:26:11.800 --> 01:26:14.724
- Can I touch you?
- [GUARD] There's no physical contact.

01:26:14.880 --> 01:26:17.531
You do touch me.

01:26:18.240 --> 01:26:22.006
Tata, I want you to know
I've always loved you,

01:26:22.160 --> 01:26:25.846
even without knowing you,
and I've always supported you,

01:26:26.000 --> 01:26:29.561
and I've always believed that one day,
you... you'll be free.

01:26:30.760 --> 01:26:32.603
We will be able to touch.

01:26:38.800 --> 01:26:40.928
[MANDELA SIGHS]

01:26:41.560 --> 01:26:44.404
You must tell our friends...

01:26:45.960 --> 01:26:48.247
that I am strong

01:26:48.400 --> 01:26:50.209
and full of hope...

01:26:52.160 --> 01:26:55.323
and eager to do
whatever is asked of me.

01:26:55.960 --> 01:26:57.564
I'll tell them.

01:26:57.720 --> 01:27:00.610
They're waiting for you.
We're all waiting for you.

01:27:02.440 --> 01:27:04.408
And we're winning support.

01:27:04.560 --> 01:27:07.370
All over the world, there's going
to be a new campaign.

01:27:07.520 --> 01:27:09.363
Free Nelson Mandela.

01:27:09.520 --> 01:27:12.603
And Walter Sisulu,

01:27:12.760 --> 01:27:14.683
and Ahmed Kathrada, all of us.

01:27:14.840 --> 01:27:18.731
[CHUCKLES]
There's no room on the badge, Tata.

01:27:18.920 --> 01:27:20.809
[CHUCKLES]

01:27:26.960 --> 01:27:29.804
[♪ GIL SCOTT-HERON:
"THE REVOLUTION WILL NOT BE TELEVISED"]

01:27:32.600 --> 01:27:36.321
South Africa needs Nelson Mandela.

01:27:36.520 --> 01:27:41.970
<i>The world needs Nelson Mandela.</i>

01:27:43.080 --> 01:27:44.366
[THUMPING]

01:27:44.520 --> 01:27:46.204
[CHANTING]

01:27:48.840 --> 01:27:50.330
[SHOUTING]

01:27:51.480 --> 01:27:52.970
[SINGING]

01:28:03.080 --> 01:28:05.321
[WHIRRING]

01:28:43.240 --> 01:28:46.403
[DISTANT SCREAMING]

01:28:48.800 --> 01:28:51.121
[SCREAMING CONTINUES, DOG BARKING]

01:28:56.920 --> 01:28:58.684
Welcome to the penthouse.

01:29:01.480 --> 01:29:04.131
- Uh, Mr. Gregory?
- Mm-hm?

01:29:04.280 --> 01:29:07.204
Do we all sleep in the same room?

01:29:07.400 --> 01:29:08.481
Yeah.

01:29:09.440 --> 01:29:11.727
Then I'm putting in for a transfer.

01:29:11.880 --> 01:29:14.406
For medical reasons.
Walter snores like a donkey.

01:29:14.560 --> 01:29:17.086
- Kathy.
- [LAUGHTER]

01:29:18.320 --> 01:29:20.482
That is what I call a big mirror.

01:29:20.640 --> 01:29:22.529
[DOOR THUMPS CLOSED, LOCK CLACKS]

01:29:22.680 --> 01:29:24.170
Ah.

01:29:25.320 --> 01:29:26.685
[MANDELA] Look at us.

01:29:26.880 --> 01:29:31.204
<i>Dangerous terrorists,
each one of us.</i>

01:29:45.480 --> 01:29:48.802
- I used to have a good right hand.
- Mmm.

01:29:48.960 --> 01:29:50.450
[CHUCKLES]

01:29:52.160 --> 01:29:54.049
<i>[CROWD CHANTING]
Winnie! Winnie! Winnie!</i>

01:29:54.240 --> 01:29:56.971
Winnie! Winnie! Winnie...!

01:30:00.560 --> 01:30:03.370
[CROWD SINGING]

01:30:32.400 --> 01:30:38.203
<i>- Amandla!
- Awethu!</i>

01:30:38.360 --> 01:30:43.082
- The army is in our townships.
- [CROWD MURMURING]

01:30:43.240 --> 01:30:46.005
Killing us every day.

01:30:46.640 --> 01:30:51.851
But we will fight
to the last drop of our blood.

01:30:52.000 --> 01:30:53.161
[SHOUTING IN AGREEMENT]

01:30:53.320 --> 01:30:56.483
We have no AK-47s.

01:30:56.680 --> 01:30:59.160
We have no Casspirs,

01:30:59.320 --> 01:31:04.087
- but we have our hands.
- [SHOUTING CONTINUES]

01:31:04.240 --> 01:31:07.323
We have stones!

01:31:07.520 --> 01:31:10.842
We have boxes of matches!

01:31:11.000 --> 01:31:12.968
We have petrol!

01:31:14.480 --> 01:31:18.201
We know the informers.

01:31:19.920 --> 01:31:22.605
We know the traitors.

01:31:23.960 --> 01:31:26.645
And we know what to do with them.

01:31:26.800 --> 01:31:29.121
[SHOUTING CONTINUES]

01:31:29.280 --> 01:31:32.090
[PANTING, CROWD SCREAMING]

01:31:36.360 --> 01:31:38.840
[SCREAMING CONTINUES]

01:31:44.280 --> 01:31:45.805
<i>[REPORTER]
In a savage killing spree,</i>

01:31:45.960 --> 01:31:48.611
<i>town officials were
torn apart by the mobs</i>

01:31:48.760 --> 01:31:51.161
<i>before the bodies were set alight.</i>

01:31:51.320 --> 01:31:53.368
[CHEERING]

01:31:56.280 --> 01:31:58.601
[SHOUTING]

01:32:01.680 --> 01:32:04.889
- [GUNSHOTS, EXPLOSIONS]
- [SCREAMING]

01:32:15.440 --> 01:32:17.283
[SHRIEKING]

01:32:21.320 --> 01:32:24.051
- [GUNSHOTS CONTINUE]
- [SCREAMING]

01:32:33.480 --> 01:32:38.122
<i>[PRESIDENT BOTHA, OVER RADIO]
I am prepared to release Mr. Mandela</i>

01:32:38.320 --> 01:32:42.450
<i>if he would say
that he rejects violence</i>

01:32:42.600 --> 01:32:48.164
<i>as a means to reach
and to achieve political ends.</i>

01:32:48.320 --> 01:32:50.049
Does he think we are idiots?

01:32:50.200 --> 01:32:53.443
Anyone can see
it's just another trick.

01:32:53.600 --> 01:32:58.561
Yes, Kathy, it is a trick,

01:32:58.760 --> 01:33:01.081
but this is how it begins.

01:33:02.400 --> 01:33:04.482
They called it a contact visit.

01:33:04.680 --> 01:33:06.409
You can touch.

01:33:09.200 --> 01:33:12.921
I haven't touched
my wife for 21 years.

01:33:15.360 --> 01:33:18.204
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING SLOWLY]

01:33:45.400 --> 01:33:47.880
[SIGHS]

01:33:51.600 --> 01:33:53.887
[SNIFFING]

01:34:09.920 --> 01:34:11.684
You haven't changed.

01:34:13.880 --> 01:34:16.884
- I have.
- No.

01:34:17.040 --> 01:34:19.441
To me, you haven't changed.

01:34:26.320 --> 01:34:29.403
Be careful this offer of release.

01:34:29.600 --> 01:34:31.364
They are using you.

01:34:31.560 --> 01:34:33.210
- I know.
- You mustn't betray

01:34:33.360 --> 01:34:35.328
our people fighting
on the streets.

01:34:35.520 --> 01:34:36.931
Speak so I can hear you.

01:34:37.080 --> 01:34:39.890
Our people have never lost hope.

01:34:41.880 --> 01:34:44.850
The more they oppress us,
the harder we fight.

01:34:46.560 --> 01:34:48.767
They fear us, Nelson.

01:34:50.360 --> 01:34:51.521
They fear me.

01:34:53.600 --> 01:34:56.763
They think you are old and tired.

01:34:56.960 --> 01:34:59.167
Make them fear you, too.

01:35:00.200 --> 01:35:02.009
No politics.

01:35:04.160 --> 01:35:05.844
We must talk politics.

01:35:06.000 --> 01:35:09.561
The president has given me an offer,
and he expects a reply.

01:35:19.000 --> 01:35:20.843
For the president.

01:35:21.840 --> 01:35:23.330
Oh, Winnie.

01:35:28.680 --> 01:35:30.409
<i>[CROWD CHEERING]</i>

01:35:31.640 --> 01:35:35.122
[SINGING, CHEERING]

01:35:50.880 --> 01:35:52.291
Oh, my comrades,

01:35:52.440 --> 01:35:55.967
- Zindzi Mandela!
- [CHEERING]

01:35:58.920 --> 01:36:03.244
On Friday, my mother saw my father

01:36:03.440 --> 01:36:06.649
in Pollsmoor Prison
and obtained his answer

01:36:06.800 --> 01:36:10.805
to President Botha's offer
of conditional release.

01:36:11.880 --> 01:36:14.531
My father says,

01:36:15.760 --> 01:36:20.288
- "I am not a violent man.
- [CHEERING]

01:36:20.440 --> 01:36:24.445
It was only when
all other forms of resistance

01:36:24.600 --> 01:36:28.446
were no longer open to us
that we turned to armed struggle."

01:36:28.600 --> 01:36:30.443
[CHEERING CONTINUES]

01:36:30.600 --> 01:36:34.207
"Let President Botha
renounce violence.

01:36:34.360 --> 01:36:38.285
- Let him dismantle apartheid."
- [CHEERING CONTINUES]

01:36:38.480 --> 01:36:40.847
"I cannot and will not

01:36:41.000 --> 01:36:45.050
give any undertaking at a time
when I and you,

01:36:45.200 --> 01:36:50.240
- the people, are not free."
- [CHEERING CONTINUES]

01:36:52.640 --> 01:36:56.645
"Your freedom and mine
cannot be separated.

01:36:57.800 --> 01:37:01.088
- I will return."
- [APPLAUSE]

01:37:03.320 --> 01:37:06.881
[CHANTING]

01:37:11.120 --> 01:37:12.963
[GROUP SINGING IN DISTANCE]

01:37:13.120 --> 01:37:16.124
<i>♪ Freedom is in your hands</i>

01:37:16.280 --> 01:37:19.170
<i>♪ Freedom is in your hands...</i>

01:37:20.480 --> 01:37:21.970
Where are we going?

01:37:39.080 --> 01:37:41.606
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

01:37:52.960 --> 01:37:54.405
Well...

01:38:01.600 --> 01:38:04.570
[WHEEZING]

01:38:08.040 --> 01:38:09.121
Welcome.

01:38:09.320 --> 01:38:12.244
My name is Kobie Coetsee.
I'm the Minister of Justice.

01:38:13.320 --> 01:38:15.846
This meeting is not taking place.

01:38:18.360 --> 01:38:20.203
The rest of the world thinks

01:38:20.360 --> 01:38:23.284
South Africa will be
ripped apart by race war.

01:38:24.680 --> 01:38:26.250
Now, uh...

01:38:26.400 --> 01:38:30.200
we have to do something
to restore confidence.

01:38:31.320 --> 01:38:34.244
Let me introduce you.
General Willemse, who you know.

01:38:34.400 --> 01:38:37.404
Fanie van der Merwe,
Prisons Department.

01:38:37.560 --> 01:38:38.925
How do you do?

01:38:39.080 --> 01:38:41.686
Dr. Niel Barnard,
National Intelligence Service.

01:38:41.840 --> 01:38:42.762
- Pleased to meet you.
- Hello.

01:38:42.920 --> 01:38:44.206
Mr. Mandela.

01:38:44.360 --> 01:38:47.443
We five are charged
by the president

01:38:47.600 --> 01:38:50.604
to find a way out
of our current difficulties.

01:38:50.760 --> 01:38:52.808
Are you sure that
you can talk to me?

01:38:52.960 --> 01:38:55.088
I am a member of
a banned organization.

01:38:55.280 --> 01:38:58.648
[CHUCKLES] Oh, we'll talk to you,
if you'll talk to us.

01:39:00.600 --> 01:39:01.931
Well, gentlemen...

01:39:05.520 --> 01:39:07.124
[SIGHS]

01:39:15.920 --> 01:39:17.570
Shall we begin?

01:39:19.000 --> 01:39:22.129
I don't trust them.
This is not the time to talk.

01:39:22.280 --> 01:39:25.602
I don't think Madiba should be
talking to them on his own.

01:39:25.760 --> 01:39:27.683
Let's just put it to the vote.

01:39:27.840 --> 01:39:30.810
I propose no private talks.

01:39:35.280 --> 01:39:36.520
And you, Walter?

01:39:36.680 --> 01:39:40.480
None of us are bigger
than the movement.

01:39:40.640 --> 01:39:42.961
Four against one. Motion carried.

01:39:43.160 --> 01:39:45.128
I take note, comrades...

01:39:46.600 --> 01:39:49.683
but I will do
what I believe is right.

01:39:51.600 --> 01:39:55.002
You have the most
powerful army in Africa.

01:39:55.160 --> 01:39:57.606
There's no way
we can match you in battle,

01:39:57.800 --> 01:40:00.406
but we have 30 million people.

01:40:00.560 --> 01:40:02.642
I would call that a stalemate.

01:40:02.800 --> 01:40:04.689
All right.

01:40:05.880 --> 01:40:08.201
Here's the bottom line:

01:40:08.360 --> 01:40:11.523
You end the violence, and we'll
give you a share in power.

01:40:14.240 --> 01:40:15.969
A share?

01:40:16.120 --> 01:40:20.762
Well, obviously, we can't accept
a crude one man, one vote system.

01:40:20.920 --> 01:40:25.960
Yeah, if the blacks take over,
our country is finished.

01:40:26.160 --> 01:40:27.446
We are finished.

01:40:27.600 --> 01:40:28.601
- Why?
- "Why?"

01:40:28.760 --> 01:40:30.569
"if the blacks take over..."

01:40:30.720 --> 01:40:32.961
Can you imagine what the
blacks would do to us

01:40:33.120 --> 01:40:34.929
if they got us in their power?

01:40:35.080 --> 01:40:36.570
I am black.

01:40:37.280 --> 01:40:39.203
You are different.

01:40:39.360 --> 01:40:42.125
That is why we are talking to you.

01:40:42.280 --> 01:40:44.282
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

01:40:45.240 --> 01:40:46.366
[KATHY] These are the same people

01:40:46.560 --> 01:40:49.643
that threw him in jail,
that persecuted his wife,

01:40:49.800 --> 01:40:53.282
that murdered his friends,
and he's talking to them.

01:40:53.480 --> 01:40:55.209
[BARNARD] I don't believe
you don't want revenge.

01:40:55.400 --> 01:40:57.323
You are right.

01:40:57.480 --> 01:40:59.130
I do.

01:40:59.320 --> 01:41:00.924
So?

01:41:01.080 --> 01:41:03.651
How can we ever allow you
to have any real power?

01:41:03.800 --> 01:41:06.929
Well, I admit I want revenge,

01:41:07.120 --> 01:41:09.691
but I want something
more than that,

01:41:09.840 --> 01:41:13.322
and that is to live
without fear and hatred.

01:41:14.280 --> 01:41:15.770
Sweet dreams, Mr. Mandela.

01:41:15.960 --> 01:41:18.850
I have no choice.

01:41:19.000 --> 01:41:21.890
I have seen what fear
has done to your people.

01:41:22.040 --> 01:41:23.929
You've always been afraid of us,

01:41:24.080 --> 01:41:27.641
and it has made you an
unjust and brutal people.

01:41:29.040 --> 01:41:31.725
Now consider our position.

01:41:32.880 --> 01:41:36.771
We know that one
day we will be free,

01:41:36.920 --> 01:41:38.888
and we will be the rulers
of our country,

01:41:39.040 --> 01:41:43.443
but do we want to live
in the same hell as you do now?

01:41:43.600 --> 01:41:45.841
That would be to
lock ourselves back

01:41:46.000 --> 01:41:50.289
into prison and our children
and generations after that.

01:41:52.280 --> 01:41:56.080
Gentlemen, look,
I can tell you for nothing,

01:41:56.240 --> 01:42:00.882
when we come to power,
there will be no revenge.

01:42:01.040 --> 01:42:03.611
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [SCREAMING]

01:42:13.160 --> 01:42:15.527
<i>[REPORTER] It's blacks that
continue to be the victims</i>

01:42:15.680 --> 01:42:17.887
<i>of this unprecedented
wave of unrest.</i>

01:42:18.040 --> 01:42:21.328
<i>Nearly 300 people have
died since September.</i>

01:42:21.480 --> 01:42:23.847
<i>Only one white has been killed.</i>

01:42:24.000 --> 01:42:26.082
<i>Police stuck to their armored
personnel carriers.</i>

01:42:26.280 --> 01:42:27.611
<i>No rubber bullets here.</i>

01:42:27.760 --> 01:42:29.728
<i>These were live rounds
they were firing.</i>

01:42:29.880 --> 01:42:32.247
Lay him there, lay him there.

01:42:34.360 --> 01:42:38.729
- [SPEAKING IN AFRICAN LANGUAGE]
- [SOBBING]

01:42:41.920 --> 01:42:44.048
He is gone, sisi.

01:42:45.920 --> 01:42:49.720
Make them suffer
as we suffer.

01:42:49.880 --> 01:42:52.042
[TRUCKS WHIRRING]

01:42:54.880 --> 01:42:57.281
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

01:43:13.840 --> 01:43:16.286
Well, you've impressed them.

01:43:17.600 --> 01:43:20.285
I think we're going
to make progress.

01:43:20.440 --> 01:43:22.124
<i>[MANDELA] I hope so.</i>

01:43:25.600 --> 01:43:29.321
<i>[COETSEE] I believe you will soon
be reaching your 70th birthday.</i>

01:43:29.480 --> 01:43:30.925
<i>My congratulations.</i>

01:43:32.960 --> 01:43:34.928
<i>Do you plan a celebration?</i>

01:43:37.880 --> 01:43:39.882
<i>[MANDELA] Nothing of consequence.</i>

01:43:45.760 --> 01:43:48.650
- Is this my new prison?
- Yeah.

01:43:54.440 --> 01:43:57.649
- Who else is to be held here?
- Just you.

01:44:13.480 --> 01:44:16.848
Ah, Mr. Mandela,
welcome to your new home.

01:44:18.200 --> 01:44:21.329
- Am I being fattened for the kill?
- [CHUCKLES]

01:44:21.520 --> 01:44:25.491
No, you have a vital job
to do for your country.

01:44:25.640 --> 01:44:27.529
We need to look after you.

01:44:29.280 --> 01:44:30.566
By the way,

01:44:30.720 --> 01:44:33.929
any members of your
family can visit any time.

01:44:34.680 --> 01:44:36.842
[LAUGHTER]

01:44:37.040 --> 01:44:40.123
Look at you kids.
She is hungry.

01:44:40.280 --> 01:44:41.520
- You are hungry.
- [CRYING]

01:44:41.680 --> 01:44:44.729
Don't make a mess, huh?
[CHUCKLES]

01:44:44.920 --> 01:44:46.570
Oh!

01:44:48.200 --> 01:44:51.329
[SPEAKING IN AFRICAN LANGUAGE]

01:44:53.400 --> 01:44:57.325
- Hello.
- [CHUCKLING]

01:45:03.400 --> 01:45:06.722
I know that it has been
tough for you, but...

01:45:07.920 --> 01:45:10.446
I hear so much these days.

01:45:11.800 --> 01:45:13.689
These boys that you
have around you.

01:45:13.840 --> 01:45:16.764
- What about them?
- Well, the violence, for one.

01:45:18.200 --> 01:45:20.806
- Some of it is necessary, but...
- [LAUGHING]

01:45:21.000 --> 01:45:22.650
Hey!

01:45:23.600 --> 01:45:25.967
Is that for me?

01:45:26.120 --> 01:45:29.602
No, Khulu.
It is for the white men.

01:45:31.600 --> 01:45:35.571
So you are doing that because
of the color of their skin?

01:45:35.760 --> 01:45:37.410
Yes, Khulu.

01:45:39.520 --> 01:45:40.407
[SIGHS]

01:45:40.600 --> 01:45:46.084
That is what they do to us,
and we must do better.

01:45:46.960 --> 01:45:50.009
- Understand?
- Yes, Khulu.

01:45:50.400 --> 01:45:52.846
Come.
Come on.

01:45:54.320 --> 01:45:56.800
These are my grandsons,

01:45:56.960 --> 01:46:00.282
and they would like to meet you.

01:46:00.440 --> 01:46:01.441
Look at him.

01:46:04.600 --> 01:46:08.685
- [SWART] I'll do that.
- No, no, I want to do it.

01:46:08.880 --> 01:46:10.450
Let Nelson do it, Swart.

01:46:10.600 --> 01:46:12.967
<i>[GREGORY OVER SPEAKER]
Swart, you can stop.</i>

01:46:14.200 --> 01:46:16.885
<i>You know that Winnie
can stay overnight</i>

01:46:17.040 --> 01:46:18.929
<i>any time that you want.</i>

01:46:19.080 --> 01:46:23.165
Yes, but she won't.
This is still a prison.

01:46:24.240 --> 01:46:26.527
She can't pretend
that I'm a free man.

01:46:26.680 --> 01:46:28.250
Maybe.

01:46:29.520 --> 01:46:32.126
But she's still your wife.

01:46:32.320 --> 01:46:35.927
Well, I was married in 1958,

01:46:36.080 --> 01:46:39.323
arrested in '62.

01:46:39.480 --> 01:46:42.211
I didn't touch her again until '84.

01:46:43.800 --> 01:46:45.564
Is she still my wife?

01:46:46.400 --> 01:46:50.962
<i>[GREGORY] I've seen you with her and
the way you look at her photograph.</i>

01:46:52.080 --> 01:46:53.844
<i>You love her.</i>

01:46:54.840 --> 01:46:58.162
<i>[MANDELA] This is very true, my friend.
I never stopped loving her.</i>

01:47:01.760 --> 01:47:03.524
<i>But I love her as she was.</i>

01:47:11.200 --> 01:47:13.168
The first step
to regaining the confidence

01:47:13.360 --> 01:47:15.249
of the markets is your release,

01:47:15.400 --> 01:47:17.721
and then, of course,
the release of your colleagues.

01:47:17.880 --> 01:47:19.120
We've briefed the president.

01:47:19.280 --> 01:47:21.282
He's a pragmatist;
he heard us.

01:47:21.440 --> 01:47:26.241
The government agrees to lift the ban
on the ANC and repeal the race laws.

01:47:26.400 --> 01:47:29.768
You undertake to renounce violence.

01:47:29.960 --> 01:47:31.849
No.

01:47:32.320 --> 01:47:36.120
- But you said...
- I said nothing.

01:47:36.280 --> 01:47:37.884
I listened.

01:47:38.480 --> 01:47:41.882
But you will withdraw your
demand for majority rule?

01:47:43.160 --> 01:47:44.286
No.

01:47:45.960 --> 01:47:48.770
Then what are you giving us
in exchange for what we give you?

01:47:49.440 --> 01:47:50.965
Nothing.

01:47:52.640 --> 01:47:55.291
These meetings have been
a complete waste of all our time.

01:47:55.440 --> 01:47:58.683
Well, I wouldn't say
that I've wasted my time.

01:48:00.560 --> 01:48:03.086
The president has made up his mind.

01:48:03.240 --> 01:48:04.765
It can't be stopped now.

01:48:11.040 --> 01:48:12.724
[SIGHS]

01:48:13.960 --> 01:48:17.726
The president is a member
of the Gereformeerde Kerk,

01:48:17.880 --> 01:48:19.609
very Calvinist.

01:48:19.800 --> 01:48:24.886
He believes God calls him to do
a special task in a special time.

01:48:26.760 --> 01:48:29.730
<i>After the inauguration service...</i>

01:48:29.880 --> 01:48:34.522
<i>he wept... and said
that God was calling him</i>

01:48:34.680 --> 01:48:37.604
<i>to save the people of South Africa.</i>

01:48:41.200 --> 01:48:43.680
- [KNOCKING ON DOOR]
- [DOOR OPENS]

01:48:43.840 --> 01:48:45.524
[MAN] President de Klerk.

01:48:46.960 --> 01:48:48.121
[SPEAKING AFRIKAANS]

01:48:50.640 --> 01:48:53.883
- It's this way.
- Hang on, shoelace.

01:48:57.640 --> 01:48:59.005
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

01:48:59.160 --> 01:49:01.083
Well, this is it.

01:49:27.600 --> 01:49:31.047
- Mr. Mandela.
- Mr. President.

01:49:31.200 --> 01:49:34.647
May I congratulate you
on your election?

01:49:34.800 --> 01:49:36.165
Thank you.

01:49:36.320 --> 01:49:40.405
You have been called
to a very special task

01:49:40.560 --> 01:49:43.245
in a very special time.

01:49:43.400 --> 01:49:45.084
So I believe.

01:49:46.480 --> 01:49:48.209
[SPEAKING AFRIKAANS]

01:49:52.080 --> 01:49:54.287
- Just here?
- Yeah.

01:49:58.360 --> 01:50:00.408
[SIGHS]

01:50:02.520 --> 01:50:08.209
Mr. Mandela, I have taken
the decision to release you.

01:50:08.360 --> 01:50:10.328
Unconditionally.

01:50:12.440 --> 01:50:16.968
A car will be ready at 9:00 tomorrow
morning to take you to the airport.

01:50:17.120 --> 01:50:20.203
A plane will be waiting to fly
you directly to Johannesburg

01:50:20.360 --> 01:50:23.489
where the official release
ceremony will take place.

01:50:25.920 --> 01:50:27.888
Mr. De Klerk,

01:50:28.040 --> 01:50:31.931
your people have taken
away half of my life

01:50:32.080 --> 01:50:34.242
and returned me an old man

01:50:34.440 --> 01:50:37.330
to a home that has
been long abandoned

01:50:37.520 --> 01:50:40.683
and a family that have
grown up without me.

01:50:42.760 --> 01:50:47.084
I don't want you at my side
at that moment.

01:50:48.520 --> 01:50:52.047
I don't want to be told that you
have given me my freedom.

01:50:53.840 --> 01:50:56.571
Just open the gate

01:50:56.720 --> 01:50:58.802
and let me go.

01:50:59.400 --> 01:51:01.482
[WIND BLOWING]

01:51:08.960 --> 01:51:10.450
[LAUGHTER]

01:51:12.120 --> 01:51:15.203
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

01:51:23.960 --> 01:51:26.770
Any minute now.
OK, Tata?

01:51:30.880 --> 01:51:32.882
Hello, hello.

01:51:34.280 --> 01:51:37.045
How are you, Auntie?
Yeah, I'm good.

01:51:40.040 --> 01:51:41.963
I wouldn't do it without you.

01:51:45.280 --> 01:51:47.248
You want me to hold your hand?

01:51:48.920 --> 01:51:50.922
In case I stumble?

01:52:01.520 --> 01:52:05.081
- [CHEERING]
- [MOTORCADE APPROACHING]

01:52:11.640 --> 01:52:14.325
[SINGING]

01:52:41.320 --> 01:52:43.607
[CHEERING INTENSIFIES]

01:53:44.440 --> 01:53:46.363
[THUMPING, SINGING]

01:54:19.640 --> 01:54:23.087
- Somebody want me?
- [CHEERING]

01:54:25.200 --> 01:54:28.682
[SINGING CONTINUES]

01:54:46.960 --> 01:54:49.850
[SINGING CONTINUES OUTSIDE]

01:54:51.360 --> 01:54:55.331
Don't be fooled by all
that cheering, Madiba.

01:54:55.480 --> 01:54:59.041
- There's anger out there.
- I know that.

01:55:07.000 --> 01:55:08.650
Winnie, Winnie.

01:55:19.600 --> 01:55:22.331
It's just been so long.

01:55:28.600 --> 01:55:30.841
It's better that way.

01:55:39.000 --> 01:55:41.321
I am so tired.

01:55:44.640 --> 01:55:46.961
I just want to sleep.

01:55:57.520 --> 01:56:00.285
[INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

01:56:04.800 --> 01:56:08.361
[♪ PUBLIC ENEMY: "FIGHT THE POWER"]

01:56:14.680 --> 01:56:18.048
The government accepts
that change must come,

01:56:18.680 --> 01:56:21.286
but I say to you again,

01:56:21.440 --> 01:56:26.128
- we must find a way to share power.
- [HECKLING]

01:56:26.640 --> 01:56:31.567
We must find a way to protect
the rights of the minorities.

01:56:35.480 --> 01:56:38.882
<i>[REPORTER] Suddenly, the illusion of
white power is beginning to crumble.</i>

01:56:39.040 --> 01:56:42.647
<i>For the first time since apartheid
began, the government here is beginning</i>

01:56:42.800 --> 01:56:46.521
<i>to talk about the need for reform,
and among ordinary white people,</i>

01:56:46.680 --> 01:56:51.004
<i>feelings now range
from bewilderment to anger to fear.</i>

01:56:51.160 --> 01:56:53.481
[MAN] De Klerk will not...
You know this.

01:56:53.640 --> 01:56:56.644
[INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

01:56:57.720 --> 01:56:58.846
[MAN] That is not going to happen.

01:56:59.000 --> 01:57:01.287
We are not sharing power
with these whites.

01:57:01.440 --> 01:57:03.124
As long as there are
white people in South Africa,

01:57:03.280 --> 01:57:06.124
- that is not going to happen.
- I mean, just how?

01:57:06.280 --> 01:57:08.487
How do we accept power
sharing with the whites?

01:57:08.640 --> 01:57:11.484
What do we do? Do we fight?
Do we start a war?

01:57:11.640 --> 01:57:13.005
We have a war!

01:57:13.160 --> 01:57:14.525
What, you think this is not a war?

01:57:14.680 --> 01:57:16.360
We have a war,
what we need now is victory.

01:57:16.400 --> 01:57:19.081
Comrades, our people can never
accept sharing power with the whites.

01:57:19.200 --> 01:57:20.725
People will not accept this.

01:57:20.880 --> 01:57:22.769
What de Klerk wants is ministers
in the new government.

01:57:22.920 --> 01:57:26.163
- Why should de Klerk get what he wants?
- De Klerk is right.

01:57:26.320 --> 01:57:28.322
We must let them share the power.

01:57:28.520 --> 01:57:33.003
A little power for a little while
until the fear has passed.

01:57:33.160 --> 01:57:35.162
Madiba, I don't think our
people will accept that.

01:57:35.360 --> 01:57:36.600
Then we must make them accept.

01:57:36.760 --> 01:57:39.570
We are their leaders.
That is our job.

01:57:39.720 --> 01:57:42.690
[CROWD CHANTING]

01:57:55.320 --> 01:57:59.530
[WINNIE] These old men
just want to talk.

01:57:59.680 --> 01:58:02.570
The days of talking are over!

01:58:02.760 --> 01:58:05.161
[CHEERING]

01:58:09.040 --> 01:58:11.008
Go and get her.

01:58:12.880 --> 01:58:15.770
[WINNIE]
I hear the voice of the people.

01:58:16.400 --> 01:58:20.041
And that voice says,
"We will fight."

01:58:20.200 --> 01:58:23.522
[CHEERING]

01:58:23.680 --> 01:58:25.921
[CROWD CHANTING]

01:58:28.040 --> 01:58:30.247
Mama,
Madiba wants to see you inside.

01:58:30.400 --> 01:58:33.085
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:58:33.240 --> 01:58:34.480
All right.

01:58:42.520 --> 01:58:44.090
What?

01:58:44.240 --> 01:58:46.766
Are you ashamed to greet me
in front of our people?

01:58:46.920 --> 01:58:48.445
Winnie, when you speak in public,

01:58:48.640 --> 01:58:51.689
you must represent
the policies of the ANC.

01:58:51.840 --> 01:58:53.720
- And what does that mean?
- We are negotiating.

01:58:53.800 --> 01:58:58.931
- We are not fighting a war.
- But the people have chosen to fight.

01:58:59.080 --> 01:59:02.004
Do you want me to
betray our people?

01:59:02.160 --> 01:59:05.767
- Do I betray our people?
- You have been away a long time.

01:59:05.920 --> 01:59:07.160
What does that mean,
I've been away?

01:59:07.320 --> 01:59:09.448
Does that mean now
you can terrorize people?

01:59:11.400 --> 01:59:15.007
The burning, the necklacing,
that has to stop, Winnie.

01:59:15.160 --> 01:59:19.882
You realize there's a war out there.
The people are angry.

01:59:20.040 --> 01:59:22.964
We are all angry.
I am angry!

01:59:23.120 --> 01:59:26.522
You are angry,
but you must show loyalty!

01:59:29.000 --> 01:59:31.924
Loyalty, Winnie Mandela.

01:59:44.280 --> 01:59:45.770
Loyalty.

01:59:51.240 --> 01:59:53.322
[SIGHS]

01:59:53.480 --> 01:59:58.042
I have decided that it would be better
if I live in my own home.

01:59:59.880 --> 02:00:01.928
Better for the party.

02:00:04.880 --> 02:00:06.370
Better for us.

02:00:10.720 --> 02:00:15.362
- "Better for the party"?
- You have your own home in Diepkloof.

02:00:18.800 --> 02:00:21.280
You have your own company there.

02:00:22.400 --> 02:00:26.121
Am I to blame because
I don't want to be alone?

02:00:27.480 --> 02:00:32.008
You know, so much
of my life,

02:00:32.200 --> 02:00:33.964
I have been alone.

02:00:35.240 --> 02:00:39.643
We have both been alone
too much, Winnie.

02:01:00.600 --> 02:01:03.729
[MANDELA] Why, Walter?
Tell me why, hmm?

02:01:03.880 --> 02:01:05.769
Why, why do you show me this?

02:01:05.920 --> 02:01:09.402
- Do you think I don't know?
- This has gone too far.

02:01:09.560 --> 02:01:13.281
- If she was discrete about this...
- I have accepted the situation!

02:01:14.480 --> 02:01:16.562
What business is
it of anyone else?

02:01:16.720 --> 02:01:21.248
She humiliates you in public, Madiba.
And that hurts all of us.

02:01:21.400 --> 02:01:22.322
Come now.

02:01:22.480 --> 02:01:27.441
<i>[MANDELA] What they have done to my
wife is their only victory over me.</i>

02:01:27.600 --> 02:01:31.571
<i>In view of the tensions
that have arisen</i>

02:01:31.760 --> 02:01:36.402
<i>between my wife and myself
in the recent months,</i>

02:01:36.600 --> 02:01:40.002
we have mutually agreed
that a separation

02:01:40.160 --> 02:01:42.845
would be best for each of us.

02:01:43.000 --> 02:01:45.924
<i>I shall personally never regret</i>

02:01:46.080 --> 02:01:50.563
<i>the life that we tried
to share together.</i>

02:01:50.720 --> 02:01:55.567
<i>I part from my wife
with no recriminations.</i>

02:01:55.720 --> 02:01:59.167
<i>I embrace her with all the love
and affection</i>

02:01:59.320 --> 02:02:03.370
<i>I have nursed for her
inside and outside of prison</i>

02:02:03.520 --> 02:02:07.206
<i>from the moment I first met her.</i>

02:02:08.680 --> 02:02:12.002
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
I hope that you can appreciate</i>

02:02:12.160 --> 02:02:13.889
<i>the pain that I am going through.</i>

02:02:14.040 --> 02:02:15.963
<i>- Thank you.
- [REPORTER] Mr. Mandela...</i>

02:02:16.120 --> 02:02:18.009
<i>[CROWD MURMURING]</i>

02:02:21.800 --> 02:02:24.883
[PHONE RINGING]

02:02:30.400 --> 02:02:33.085
- [SIGHS]
- [RINGING CONTINUES]

02:02:33.280 --> 02:02:35.282
- [EXPLOSIONS]
- [YELLING]

02:02:35.440 --> 02:02:36.362
[PHONE RINGING]

02:02:36.520 --> 02:02:39.603
<i>[REPORTER] Police opened fire
on gun-carrying demonstrators...</i>

02:02:39.760 --> 02:02:43.651
Mr. Mandela?
President de Klerk here.

02:02:43.800 --> 02:02:46.565
The situation on the streets
is out of control.

02:02:46.720 --> 02:02:49.166
Is this the peaceful
South Africa you say you want?

02:02:49.320 --> 02:02:50.685
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [SCREAMING]

02:02:50.880 --> 02:02:54.202
<i>[REPORTER] Black-on-black violence has</i>
<i>reached proportions of near civil war.</i>

02:02:54.360 --> 02:02:56.488
[SHOUTING]

02:02:56.680 --> 02:02:59.001
<i>They began fighting as the
power struggle developed</i>

02:02:59.160 --> 02:03:02.130
<i>in South Africa to replace
white rule with black.</i>

02:03:02.280 --> 02:03:05.921
<i>[REPORTER 2] Two hundred Zulus
rampaged through Boipatong,</i>

02:03:06.080 --> 02:03:07.320
<i>cutting down anyone they saw.</i>

02:03:07.520 --> 02:03:10.046
[screaming]

02:03:34.000 --> 02:03:37.288
- [SOBBING]
- [DISTANT SINGING]

02:03:59.240 --> 02:04:02.164
[SOBBING CONTINUES]

02:05:00.840 --> 02:05:03.161
Madiba, do something.

02:05:04.160 --> 02:05:07.050
[SPEAKS IN AFRICAN LANGUAGE]

02:05:08.640 --> 02:05:09.766
Do something.

02:05:09.920 --> 02:05:12.082
Do something, do something.

02:05:19.440 --> 02:05:21.488
<i>[REPORTER] President de Klerk blames
the Boipatong massacre...</i>

02:05:21.640 --> 02:05:23.404
<i>[REPORTER 2] ...attacks by the Inkatha
Freedom Party supporters</i>

02:05:23.560 --> 02:05:27.087
<i>on an ANC rally near Johannesburg
has left 13 people dead.</i>

02:05:27.240 --> 02:05:29.607
<i>[REPORTER 3] It could set back
the peace process in South Africa</i>

02:05:29.760 --> 02:05:31.171
<i>by months, if not years.</i>

02:05:31.320 --> 02:05:34.403
<i>[REPORTER 4] ...violence has now put
South Africa's constitution...</i>

02:05:34.560 --> 02:05:37.370
<i>[REPORTER 5] ...de Klerk has attacked
what he calls "the ultimatum politics"</i>

02:05:37.520 --> 02:05:38.601
<i>of the ANC.</i>

02:05:38.800 --> 02:05:42.009
<i>[REPORTER 6] Increasing financial
and diplomatic isolation...</i>

02:05:42.160 --> 02:05:45.403
<i>- Please sit down.
- [REPORTER SPEAKING AFRIKAANS]</i>

02:05:45.600 --> 02:05:47.682
<i>[REPORTER 7] ...today's move on Capitol
Hill, the indications...</i>

02:05:47.840 --> 02:05:50.764
Mr. Mandela, you're going to be
talking into that camera.

02:05:50.920 --> 02:05:53.127
- Yes, this one.
- A little bit more light please.

02:05:53.280 --> 02:05:55.089
Yeah, lovely, you see?

02:05:55.240 --> 02:05:58.130
<i>[VARIOUS BROADCAST REPORTS OVERLAPPING]</i>

02:05:58.320 --> 02:06:00.288
<i>[REPORTER 8] ...wondering whether
it can survive the rage</i>

02:06:00.440 --> 02:06:02.080
<i>that divides that nation,
black and white.</i>

02:06:02.200 --> 02:06:04.961
<i>[REPORTER 9] ...but it does not derail
talks toward ending white rule.</i>

02:06:05.040 --> 02:06:06.690
<i>[REPORTER 10] South African president,
FW de Klerk...</i>

02:06:06.840 --> 02:06:08.729
<i>[REPORTER 11] Panic, chaos, confusion...</i>

02:06:08.880 --> 02:06:10.120
<i>[REPORTER 12]
...white minority's worst nightmare.</i>

02:06:10.280 --> 02:06:11.520
<i>[REPORT 11]
...crisis for this country...</i>

02:06:11.680 --> 02:06:14.001
[WOMAN] Five seconds, four,

02:06:14.160 --> 02:06:16.049
three, two...

02:06:19.000 --> 02:06:22.971
Someone gave me this note...

02:06:24.440 --> 02:06:27.330
when I was leaving Boipatong...

02:06:29.160 --> 02:06:31.606
and I want to read it to you.

02:06:33.000 --> 02:06:34.889
It says,

02:06:35.040 --> 02:06:36.963
"No peace.

02:06:38.560 --> 02:06:43.441
Do not talk about peace.

02:06:43.600 --> 02:06:45.728
We have had enough.

02:06:45.880 --> 02:06:48.486
Please, Mr. Mandela,

02:06:48.640 --> 02:06:50.802
no peace.

02:06:51.800 --> 02:06:54.406
Give us weapons,

02:06:54.560 --> 02:06:56.483
not peace."

02:07:01.480 --> 02:07:03.642
Here is my answer.

02:07:03.840 --> 02:07:05.968
[CLOCK TICKING]

02:07:08.560 --> 02:07:12.531
There is only one way forward,

02:07:12.680 --> 02:07:15.684
and that is peace.

02:07:15.840 --> 02:07:18.161
[SHOUTING]

02:07:20.920 --> 02:07:25.482
I know that is not
what you want to hear,

02:07:25.640 --> 02:07:29.645
but there is no other way.

02:07:30.840 --> 02:07:33.161
<i>I am your leader,</i>

02:07:33.320 --> 02:07:36.722
<i>and as long as I am your leader,</i>

02:07:36.880 --> 02:07:39.770
<i>I'm going to give you leadership.</i>

02:07:40.960 --> 02:07:44.567
As long as I am your leader,

02:07:44.760 --> 02:07:48.731
I am going to tell you always

02:07:48.880 --> 02:07:49.927
when you are wrong,

02:07:50.080 --> 02:07:54.085
<i>and I tell you now,
you are wrong.</i>

02:07:54.240 --> 02:07:56.368
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

02:07:56.560 --> 02:08:00.804
<i>I have given my
life to the struggle.</i>

02:08:01.560 --> 02:08:04.131
<i>I've been willing to die.</i>

02:08:04.320 --> 02:08:08.689
<i>I have lost 27 years of my life</i>

02:08:08.840 --> 02:08:10.285
<i>in prison,</i>

02:08:10.440 --> 02:08:14.126
<i>but I tell you now,</i>

02:08:14.280 --> 02:08:17.648
<i>I have forgiven them.</i>

02:08:17.800 --> 02:08:19.211
[SHOUTING]

02:08:20.680 --> 02:08:23.365
If I can forgive them...

02:08:25.560 --> 02:08:28.769
then you can forgive them.

02:08:33.400 --> 02:08:37.200
We cannot win a war,

02:08:37.360 --> 02:08:42.446
but we can win an election.

02:08:43.720 --> 02:08:46.690
So, my people...

02:08:47.800 --> 02:08:49.529
stay home...

02:08:51.200 --> 02:08:52.690
be peaceful,

02:08:52.840 --> 02:08:56.049
and when election day comes...

02:08:58.040 --> 02:08:59.644
vote.

02:09:01.800 --> 02:09:04.087
- Cut there.
- Ja, we've cut.

02:09:11.400 --> 02:09:17.282
[SPEAKING IN AFRIKAANS]

02:09:23.960 --> 02:09:26.042
[SHUDDERS]

02:09:34.360 --> 02:09:37.682
<i>[MANDELA] After so much suffering,
why would anyone believe</i>

02:09:37.840 --> 02:09:40.684
<i>that putting a mark on
a piece of paper...</i>

02:09:42.480 --> 02:09:44.687
<i>is going to change the world?</i>

02:09:54.440 --> 02:09:57.922
[UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING]

02:10:03.760 --> 02:10:05.808
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

02:10:11.720 --> 02:10:14.644
[CHEERING]

02:10:25.440 --> 02:10:27.090
[CHEERING]

02:10:30.560 --> 02:10:32.483
[CHEERING]

02:10:44.800 --> 02:10:47.451
[CHEERING]

02:11:11.960 --> 02:11:15.931
[CROWD CHANTING, SINGING]

02:11:21.320 --> 02:11:23.800
<i>[CHILD SHOUTING IN DISTANCE]</i>

02:11:25.040 --> 02:11:28.761
<i>[MANDELA]
I still dream the old dream,</i>

02:11:30.440 --> 02:11:33.523
<i>back in the house in Orlando.</i>

02:11:35.120 --> 02:11:40.604
<i>I can hear all the ones
that I have loved most in the world.</i>

02:11:40.760 --> 02:11:42.091
[LAUGHTER ECHOING]

02:11:42.240 --> 02:11:43.685
<i>I want to reach them...</i>

02:11:45.040 --> 02:11:46.644
<i>to touch them...</i>

02:11:48.760 --> 02:11:52.242
<i>- ...but they have gone.
- [BABY COOING]</i>

02:11:54.040 --> 02:11:56.361
<i>[CHILD, ECHOING] Tata...</i>

02:12:00.040 --> 02:12:01.804
[SIGHS]

02:12:05.240 --> 02:12:08.642
[MAN]
Madiba, are you ready for this?

02:12:26.760 --> 02:12:29.525
[CLICKING]

02:12:29.680 --> 02:12:32.729
- These are my jailers now.
- [LAUGHTER]

02:12:32.920 --> 02:12:34.521
[WOMAN] This is a proud day,
Mr. Mandela.

02:12:34.560 --> 02:12:35.686
[MANDELA] Feels good.

02:13:05.240 --> 02:13:09.006
[CHEERING, APPLAUSE]

02:13:26.040 --> 02:13:28.566
[CHEERING, APPLAUSE FADES]

02:13:37.400 --> 02:13:41.803
<i>[MANDELA] I have walked
a long walk to freedom.</i>

02:13:44.160 --> 02:13:47.881
<i>It has been a lonely road...</i>

02:13:49.160 --> 02:13:52.562
<i>- ...and it is not over yet.
- [CHILDREN CHATTERING]</i>

02:13:52.720 --> 02:13:56.088
<i>I know that my country</i>

02:13:56.240 --> 02:13:59.767
<i>was not made to be a land of hatred.</i>

02:14:01.800 --> 02:14:05.805
<i>No one is born hating
another person</i>

02:14:05.960 --> 02:14:08.611
<i>because of the color of his skin.</i>

02:14:10.360 --> 02:14:13.204
<i>People learn to hate.</i>

02:14:15.720 --> 02:14:19.645
<i>They can be taught to love,</i>

02:14:19.800 --> 02:14:25.045
<i>for love comes more naturally</i>

02:14:25.240 --> 02:14:27.163
<i>to the human heart.</i>

02:14:38.160 --> 02:14:42.563
[♪ U2: "ORDINARY LOVE"]

